var book = {
	"name": "Leviticus",
	"numChapters": 27,
	"chapters": {
		"1": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">1 </span>The <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> called to Moses<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-2747A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-2747A\"></sup> and spoke to him from the tent of meeting.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-2747B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-2747B\"></sup> He said,",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>“Speak to the Israelites and say to them: ‘When anyone among you brings an offering to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-2748C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-2748C\"></sup> bring as your offering an animal from either the herd or the flock.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-2748D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-2748D\"></sup>",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>“‘If the offering is a burnt offering<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-2749E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-2749E\"></sup> from the herd,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-2749F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-2749F\"></sup> you are to offer a male without defect.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-2749G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-2749G\"></sup> You must present it at the entrance to the tent<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-2749H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-2749H\"></sup> of meeting so that it will be acceptable<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-2749I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-2749I\"></sup> to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>You are to lay your hand on the head<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-2750J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-2750J\"></sup> of the burnt offering,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-2750K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-2750K\"></sup> and it will be accepted<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-2750L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-2750L\"></sup> on your behalf to make atonement<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-2750M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-2750M\"></sup> for you.",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>You are to slaughter<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-2751N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-2751N\"></sup> the young bull<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-2751O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-2751O\"></sup> before the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, and then Aaron’s sons<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-2751P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-2751P\"></sup> the priests shall bring the blood and splash it against the sides of the altar<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-2751Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-2751Q\"></sup> at the entrance to the tent of meeting.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>You are to skin<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-2752R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-2752R\"></sup> the burnt offering and cut it into pieces.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-2752S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-2752S\"></sup>",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>The sons of Aaron the priest are to put fire on the altar and arrange wood<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-2753T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-2753T\"></sup> on the fire.",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>Then Aaron’s sons the priests shall arrange the pieces, including the head and the fat,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-2754U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-2754U\"></sup> on the wood<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-2754V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-2754V\"></sup> that is burning on the altar.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>You are to wash the internal organs and the legs with water,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-2755W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-2755W\"></sup> and the priest is to burn all of it<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-2755X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-2755X\"></sup> on the altar.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-2755Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-2755Y\"></sup> It is a burnt offering,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-2755Z&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Z&quot;&gt;Z&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-2755Z\"></sup> a food offering,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-2755AA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AA&quot;&gt;AA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-2755AA\"></sup> an aroma pleasing to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-2755AB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AB&quot;&gt;AB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-2755AB\"></sup>",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>“‘If the offering is a burnt offering from the flock, from either the sheep<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-2756AC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AC&quot;&gt;AC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-2756AC\"></sup> or the goats,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-2756AD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AD&quot;&gt;AD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-2756AD\"></sup> you are to offer a male without defect.",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>You are to slaughter it at the north side of the altar<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-2757AE&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AE&quot;&gt;AE&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-2757AE\"></sup> before the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, and Aaron’s sons the priests shall splash its blood against the sides of the altar.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-2757AF&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AF&quot;&gt;AF&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-2757AF\"></sup>",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>You are to cut it into pieces, and the priest shall arrange them, including the head and the fat,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-2758AG&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AG&quot;&gt;AG&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-2758AG\"></sup> on the wood that is burning on the altar.",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>You are to wash the internal organs and the legs with water,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-2759AH&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AH&quot;&gt;AH&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-2759AH\"></sup> and the priest is to bring all of them and burn them<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-2759AI&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AI&quot;&gt;AI&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-2759AI\"></sup> on the altar.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-2759AJ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AJ&quot;&gt;AJ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-2759AJ\"></sup> It is a burnt offering,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-2759AK&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AK&quot;&gt;AK&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-2759AK\"></sup> a food offering, an aroma pleasing to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>“‘If the offering to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> is a burnt offering of birds, you are to offer a dove or a young pigeon.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-2760AL&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AL&quot;&gt;AL&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-2760AL\"></sup>",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>The priest shall bring it to the altar, wring off the head<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-2761AM&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AM&quot;&gt;AM&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-2761AM\"></sup> and burn it on the altar; its blood shall be drained out on the side of the altar.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-2761AN&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AN&quot;&gt;AN&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-2761AN\"></sup>",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>He is to remove the crop and the feathers and throw them down east of the altar where the ashes<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-2762AO&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AO&quot;&gt;AO&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-2762AO\"></sup> are.",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>He shall tear it open by the wings, not dividing it completely,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-2763AP&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AP&quot;&gt;AP&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-2763AP\"></sup> and then the priest shall burn it on the wood<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-2763AQ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AQ&quot;&gt;AQ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-2763AQ\"></sup> that is burning on the altar. It is a burnt offering, a food offering, an aroma pleasing to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>."
		},
		"2": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">2 </span>“‘When anyone brings a grain offering<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-2764A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-2764A\"></sup> to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, their offering is to be of the finest flour.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-2764B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-2764B\"></sup> They are to pour olive oil<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-2764C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-2764C\"></sup> on it,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-2764D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-2764D\"></sup> put incense on it<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-2764E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-2764E\"></sup>",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>and take it to Aaron’s sons the priests. The priest shall take a handful of the flour<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-2765F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-2765F\"></sup> and oil, together with all the incense,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-2765G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-2765G\"></sup> and burn this as a memorial portion<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-2765H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-2765H\"></sup> on the altar, a food offering,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-2765I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-2765I\"></sup> an aroma pleasing to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-2765J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-2765J\"></sup>",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>The rest of the grain offering belongs to Aaron and his sons;<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-2766K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-2766K\"></sup> it is a most holy<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-2766L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-2766L\"></sup> part of the food offerings presented to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>“‘If you bring a grain offering baked in an oven,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-2767M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-2767M\"></sup> it is to consist of the finest flour: either thick loaves made without yeast and with olive oil mixed in or thin loaves<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-2767N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-2767N\"></sup> made without yeast and brushed with olive oil.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-2767O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-2767O\"></sup>",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>If your grain offering is prepared on a griddle,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-2768P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-2768P\"></sup> it is to be made of the finest flour mixed with oil, and without yeast.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>Crumble it and pour oil on it; it is a grain offering.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>If your grain offering is cooked in a pan,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-2770Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-2770Q\"></sup> it is to be made of the finest flour and some olive oil.",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>Bring the grain offering made of these things to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>; present it to the priest, who shall take it to the altar.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>He shall take out the memorial portion<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-2772R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-2772R\"></sup> from the grain offering and burn it on the altar as a food offering, an aroma pleasing to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-2772S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-2772S\"></sup>",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>The rest of the grain offering belongs to Aaron and his sons;<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-2773T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-2773T\"></sup> it is a most holy part of the food offerings presented to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-2773U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-2773U\"></sup>",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>“‘Every grain offering you bring to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> must be made without yeast,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-2774V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-2774V\"></sup> for you are not to burn any yeast or honey in a food offering presented to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>You may bring them to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> as an offering of the firstfruits,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-2775W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-2775W\"></sup> but they are not to be offered on the altar as a pleasing aroma.",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>Season all your grain offerings with salt.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-2776X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-2776X\"></sup> Do not leave the salt of the covenant<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-2776Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-2776Y\"></sup> of your God out of your grain offerings; add salt to all your offerings.",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>“‘If you bring a grain offering of firstfruits<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-2777Z&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Z&quot;&gt;Z&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-2777Z\"></sup> to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, offer crushed heads of new grain roasted in the fire.",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>Put oil and incense<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-2778AA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AA&quot;&gt;AA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-2778AA\"></sup> on it; it is a grain offering.",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>The priest shall burn the memorial portion<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-2779AB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AB&quot;&gt;AB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-2779AB\"></sup> of the crushed grain and the oil, together with all the incense,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-2779AC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AC&quot;&gt;AC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-2779AC\"></sup> as a food offering presented to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-2779AD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AD&quot;&gt;AD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-2779AD\"></sup>"
		},
		"3": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">3 </span>“‘If your offering is a fellowship offering,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-2780A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-2780A\"></sup> and you offer an animal from the herd, whether male or female, you are to present before the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> an animal without defect.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-2780B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-2780B\"></sup>",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>You are to lay your hand on the head<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-2781C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-2781C\"></sup> of your offering and slaughter it<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-2781D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-2781D\"></sup> at the entrance to the tent of meeting.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-2781E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-2781E\"></sup> Then Aaron’s sons the priests shall splash<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-2781F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-2781F\"></sup> the blood against the sides<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-2781G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-2781G\"></sup> of the altar.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-2781H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-2781H\"></sup>",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>From the fellowship offering you are to bring a food offering to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>: the internal organs<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-2782I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-2782I\"></sup> and all the fat<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-2782J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-2782J\"></sup> that is connected to them,",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>both kidneys<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-2783K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-2783K\"></sup> with the fat on them near the loins, and the long lobe of the liver, which you will remove with the kidneys.",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>Then Aaron’s sons<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-2784L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-2784L\"></sup> are to burn it on the altar<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-2784M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-2784M\"></sup> on top of the burnt offering<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-2784N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-2784N\"></sup> that is lying on the burning wood;<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-2784O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-2784O\"></sup> it is a food offering, an aroma pleasing to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-2784P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-2784P\"></sup>",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>“‘If you offer an animal from the flock as a fellowship offering<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-2785Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-2785Q\"></sup> to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, you are to offer a male or female without defect.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>If you offer a lamb,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-2786R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-2786R\"></sup> you are to present it before the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-2786S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-2786S\"></sup>",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>lay your hand on its head and slaughter it<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-2787T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-2787T\"></sup> in front of the tent of meeting. Then Aaron’s sons shall splash its blood against the sides of the altar.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>From the fellowship offering you are to bring a food offering<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-2788U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-2788U\"></sup> to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>: its fat, the entire fat tail cut off close to the backbone, the internal organs and all the fat that is connected to them,",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>both kidneys with the fat on them near the loins, and the long lobe of the liver, which you will remove with the kidneys.",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>The priest shall burn them on the altar<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-2790V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-2790V\"></sup> as a food offering<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-2790W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-2790W\"></sup> presented to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-2790X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-2790X\"></sup>",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>“‘If your offering is a goat,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-2791Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-2791Y\"></sup> you are to present it before the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>,",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>lay your hand on its head and slaughter it in front of the tent of meeting. Then Aaron’s sons shall splash<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-2792Z&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Z&quot;&gt;Z&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-2792Z\"></sup> its blood against the sides of the altar.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-2792AA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AA&quot;&gt;AA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-2792AA\"></sup>",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>From what you offer you are to present this food offering to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>: the internal organs and all the fat that is connected to them,",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>both kidneys with the fat on them near the loins, and the long lobe of the liver, which you will remove with the kidneys.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-2794AB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AB&quot;&gt;AB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-2794AB\"></sup>",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>The priest shall burn them on the altar<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-2795AC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AC&quot;&gt;AC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-2795AC\"></sup> as a food offering,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-2795AD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AD&quot;&gt;AD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-2795AD\"></sup> a pleasing aroma.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-2795AE&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AE&quot;&gt;AE&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-2795AE\"></sup> All the fat<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-2795AF&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AF&quot;&gt;AF&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-2795AF\"></sup> is the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>’s.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-2795AG&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AG&quot;&gt;AG&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-2795AG\"></sup>",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>“‘This is a lasting ordinance<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-2796AH&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AH&quot;&gt;AH&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-2796AH\"></sup> for the generations to come,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-2796AI&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AI&quot;&gt;AI&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-2796AI\"></sup> wherever you live:<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-2796AJ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AJ&quot;&gt;AJ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-2796AJ\"></sup> You must not eat any fat or any blood.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-2796AK&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AK&quot;&gt;AK&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-2796AK\"></sup>’”"
		},
		"4": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">4 </span>The <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> said to Moses,",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>“Say to the Israelites: ‘When anyone sins unintentionally<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-2798A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-2798A\"></sup> and does what is forbidden in any of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>’s commands<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-2798B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-2798B\"></sup>—",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>“‘If the anointed priest<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-2799C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-2799C\"></sup> sins,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-2799D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-2799D\"></sup> bringing guilt on the people, he must bring to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> a young bull<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-2799E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-2799E\"></sup> without defect<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-2799F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-2799F\"></sup> as a sin offering<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-2799G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-2799G\"></sup> for the sin he has committed.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-2799H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-2799H\"></sup>",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>He is to present the bull at the entrance to the tent of meeting before the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-2800I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-2800I\"></sup> He is to lay his hand on its head and slaughter it there before the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>Then the anointed priest shall take some of the bull’s blood<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-2801J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-2801J\"></sup> and carry it into the tent of meeting.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>He is to dip his finger into the blood and sprinkle<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-2802K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-2802K\"></sup> some of it seven times before the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-2802L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-2802L\"></sup> in front of the curtain of the sanctuary.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-2802M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-2802M\"></sup>",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>The priest shall then put some of the blood on the horns<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-2803N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-2803N\"></sup> of the altar of fragrant incense that is before the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> in the tent of meeting. The rest of the bull’s blood he shall pour out at the base of the altar<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-2803O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-2803O\"></sup> of burnt offering<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-2803P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-2803P\"></sup> at the entrance to the tent of meeting.",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>He shall remove all the fat<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-2804Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-2804Q\"></sup> from the bull of the sin offering—all the fat that is connected to the internal organs,",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>both kidneys with the fat on them near the loins, and the long lobe of the liver, which he will remove with the kidneys<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-2805R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-2805R\"></sup>—",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>just as the fat is removed from the ox<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-2806S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-2806S\"></sup> sacrificed as a fellowship offering.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-2806T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-2806T\"></sup> Then the priest shall burn them on the altar of burnt offering.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-2806U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-2806U\"></sup>",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>But the hide of the bull and all its flesh, as well as the head and legs, the internal organs and the intestines<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-2807V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-2807V\"></sup>—",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>that is, all the rest of the bull—he must take outside the camp<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-2808W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-2808W\"></sup> to a place ceremonially clean,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-2808X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-2808X\"></sup> where the ashes<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-2808Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-2808Y\"></sup> are thrown, and burn it<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-2808Z&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Z&quot;&gt;Z&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-2808Z\"></sup> there in a wood fire on the ash heap.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-2808AA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AA&quot;&gt;AA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-2808AA\"></sup>",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>“‘If the whole Israelite community sins unintentionally<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-2809AB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AB&quot;&gt;AB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-2809AB\"></sup> and does what is forbidden in any of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>’s commands, even though the community is unaware of the matter, when they realize their guilt",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>and the sin they committed becomes known, the assembly must bring a young bull<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-2810AC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AC&quot;&gt;AC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-2810AC\"></sup> as a sin offering<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-2810AD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AD&quot;&gt;AD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-2810AD\"></sup> and present it before the tent of meeting.",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>The elders<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-2811AE&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AE&quot;&gt;AE&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-2811AE\"></sup> of the community are to lay their hands<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-2811AF&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AF&quot;&gt;AF&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-2811AF\"></sup> on the bull’s head<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-2811AG&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AG&quot;&gt;AG&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-2811AG\"></sup> before the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, and the bull shall be slaughtered before the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-2811AH&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AH&quot;&gt;AH&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-2811AH\"></sup>",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>Then the anointed priest is to take some of the bull’s blood<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-2812AI&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AI&quot;&gt;AI&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-2812AI\"></sup> into the tent of meeting.",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>He shall dip his finger into the blood and sprinkle<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-2813AJ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AJ&quot;&gt;AJ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-2813AJ\"></sup> it before the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-2813AK&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AK&quot;&gt;AK&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-2813AK\"></sup> seven times in front of the curtain.",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>He is to put some of the blood<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-2814AL&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AL&quot;&gt;AL&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-2814AL\"></sup> on the horns of the altar that is before the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-2814AM&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AM&quot;&gt;AM&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-2814AM\"></sup> in the tent of meeting. The rest of the blood he shall pour out at the base of the altar<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-2814AN&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AN&quot;&gt;AN&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-2814AN\"></sup> of burnt offering at the entrance to the tent of meeting.",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>He shall remove all the fat<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-2815AO&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AO&quot;&gt;AO&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-2815AO\"></sup> from it and burn it on the altar,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-2815AP&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AP&quot;&gt;AP&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-2815AP\"></sup>",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>and do with this bull just as he did with the bull for the sin offering. In this way the priest will make atonement<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-2816AQ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AQ&quot;&gt;AQ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-2816AQ\"></sup> for the community, and they will be forgiven.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-2816AR&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AR&quot;&gt;AR&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-2816AR\"></sup>",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>Then he shall take the bull outside the camp<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-2817AS&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AS&quot;&gt;AS&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-2817AS\"></sup> and burn it as he burned the first bull. This is the sin offering for the community.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-2817AT&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AT&quot;&gt;AT&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-2817AT\"></sup>",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>“‘When a leader<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-2818AU&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AU&quot;&gt;AU&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-2818AU\"></sup> sins unintentionally<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-2818AV&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AV&quot;&gt;AV&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-2818AV\"></sup> and does what is forbidden in any of the commands of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> his God, when he realizes his guilt",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>and the sin he has committed becomes known, he must bring as his offering a male goat<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-2819AW&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AW&quot;&gt;AW&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-2819AW\"></sup> without defect.",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup>He is to lay his hand on the goat’s head and slaughter it at the place where the burnt offering is slaughtered before the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-2820AX&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AX&quot;&gt;AX&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-2820AX\"></sup> It is a sin offering.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-2820AY&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AY&quot;&gt;AY&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-2820AY\"></sup>",
			"25": "<sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup>Then the priest shall take some of the blood of the sin offering with his finger and put it on the horns of the altar<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-2821AZ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AZ&quot;&gt;AZ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-2821AZ\"></sup> of burnt offering and pour out the rest of the blood at the base of the altar.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-2821BA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BA&quot;&gt;BA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-2821BA\"></sup>",
			"26": "<sup class=\"versenum\">26 </sup>He shall burn all the fat on the altar as he burned the fat of the fellowship offering. In this way the priest will make atonement<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-2822BB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BB&quot;&gt;BB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-2822BB\"></sup> for the leader’s sin, and he will be forgiven.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-2822BC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BC&quot;&gt;BC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-2822BC\"></sup>",
			"27": "<sup class=\"versenum\">27 </sup>“‘If any member of the community sins unintentionally<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-2823BD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BD&quot;&gt;BD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-2823BD\"></sup> and does what is forbidden in any of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>’s commands, when they realize their guilt",
			"28": "<sup class=\"versenum\">28 </sup>and the sin they have committed becomes known, they must bring as their offering<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-2824BE&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BE&quot;&gt;BE&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-2824BE\"></sup> for the sin they committed a female goat<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-2824BF&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BF&quot;&gt;BF&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-2824BF\"></sup> without defect.",
			"29": "<sup class=\"versenum\">29 </sup>They are to lay their hand on the head<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-2825BG&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BG&quot;&gt;BG&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-2825BG\"></sup> of the sin offering<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-2825BH&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BH&quot;&gt;BH&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-2825BH\"></sup> and slaughter it at the place of the burnt offering.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-2825BI&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BI&quot;&gt;BI&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-2825BI\"></sup>",
			"30": "<sup class=\"versenum\">30 </sup>Then the priest is to take some of the blood with his finger and put it on the horns of the altar of burnt offering<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-2826BJ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BJ&quot;&gt;BJ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-2826BJ\"></sup> and pour out the rest of the blood at the base of the altar.",
			"31": "<sup class=\"versenum\">31 </sup>They shall remove all the fat, just as the fat is removed from the fellowship offering, and the priest shall burn it on the altar<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-2827BK&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BK&quot;&gt;BK&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-2827BK\"></sup> as an aroma pleasing to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-2827BL&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BL&quot;&gt;BL&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-2827BL\"></sup> In this way the priest will make atonement<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-2827BM&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BM&quot;&gt;BM&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-2827BM\"></sup> for them, and they will be forgiven.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-2827BN&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BN&quot;&gt;BN&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-2827BN\"></sup>",
			"32": "<sup class=\"versenum\">32 </sup>“‘If someone brings a lamb<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-2828BO&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BO&quot;&gt;BO&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-2828BO\"></sup> as their sin offering, they are to bring a female without defect.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-2828BP&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BP&quot;&gt;BP&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-2828BP\"></sup>",
			"33": "<sup class=\"versenum\">33 </sup>They are to lay their hand on its head and slaughter it<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-2829BQ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BQ&quot;&gt;BQ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-2829BQ\"></sup> for a sin offering<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-2829BR&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BR&quot;&gt;BR&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-2829BR\"></sup> at the place where the burnt offering is slaughtered.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-2829BS&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BS&quot;&gt;BS&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-2829BS\"></sup>",
			"34": "<sup class=\"versenum\">34 </sup>Then the priest shall take some of the blood of the sin offering with his finger and put it on the horns of the altar of burnt offering and pour out the rest of the blood at the base of the altar.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-2830BT&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BT&quot;&gt;BT&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-2830BT\"></sup>",
			"35": "<sup class=\"versenum\">35 </sup>They shall remove all the fat, just as the fat is removed from the lamb of the fellowship offering, and the priest shall burn it on the altar<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-2831BU&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BU&quot;&gt;BU&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-2831BU\"></sup> on top of the food offerings presented to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>. In this way the priest will make atonement for them for the sin they have committed, and they will be forgiven."
		},
		"5": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">5 </span>“‘If anyone sins because they do not speak up when they hear a public charge to testify<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-2832A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-2832A\"></sup> regarding something they have seen or learned about, they will be held responsible.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-2832B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-2832B\"></sup>",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>“‘If anyone becomes aware that they are guilty—if they unwittingly touch anything ceremonially unclean (whether the carcass of an unclean animal, wild or domestic, or of any unclean creature that moves along the ground)<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-2833C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-2833C\"></sup> and they are unaware that they have become unclean,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-2833D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-2833D\"></sup> but then they come to realize their guilt;",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>or if they touch human uncleanness<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-2834E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-2834E\"></sup> (anything that would make them unclean)<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-2834F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-2834F\"></sup> even though they are unaware of it, but then they learn of it and realize their guilt;",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>or if anyone thoughtlessly takes an oath<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-2835G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-2835G\"></sup> to do anything, whether good or evil<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-2835H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-2835H\"></sup> (in any matter one might carelessly swear about) even though they are unaware of it, but then they learn of it and realize their guilt—",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>when anyone becomes aware that they are guilty in any of these matters, they must confess<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-2836I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-2836I\"></sup> in what way they have sinned.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>As a penalty for the sin they have committed, they must bring to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> a female lamb or goat<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-2837J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-2837J\"></sup> from the flock as a sin offering;<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-2837K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-2837K\"></sup> and the priest shall make atonement<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-2837L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-2837L\"></sup> for them for their sin.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>“‘Anyone who cannot afford<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-2838M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-2838M\"></sup> a lamb<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-2838N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-2838N\"></sup> is to bring two doves or two young pigeons<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-2838O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-2838O\"></sup> to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> as a penalty for their sin—one for a sin offering and the other for a burnt offering.",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>They are to bring them to the priest, who shall first offer the one for the sin offering. He is to wring its head from its neck,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-2839P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-2839P\"></sup> not dividing it completely,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-2839Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-2839Q\"></sup>",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>and is to splash<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-2840R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-2840R\"></sup> some of the blood of the sin offering against the side of the altar;<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-2840S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-2840S\"></sup> the rest of the blood must be drained out at the base of the altar.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-2840T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-2840T\"></sup> It is a sin offering.",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>The priest shall then offer the other as a burnt offering in the prescribed way<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-2841U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-2841U\"></sup> and make atonement<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-2841V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-2841V\"></sup> for them for the sin they have committed, and they will be forgiven.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-2841W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-2841W\"></sup>",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>“‘If, however, they cannot afford<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-2842X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-2842X\"></sup> two doves or two young pigeons,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-2842Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-2842Y\"></sup> they are to bring as an offering for their sin a tenth of an ephah<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-2842Z&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Z&quot;&gt;Z&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-2842Z\"></sup> of the finest flour<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-2842AA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AA&quot;&gt;AA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-2842AA\"></sup> for a sin offering. They must not put olive oil or incense on it, because it is a sin offering.",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>They are to bring it to the priest, who shall take a handful of it as a memorial portion<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-2843AB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AB&quot;&gt;AB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-2843AB\"></sup> and burn it on the altar<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-2843AC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AC&quot;&gt;AC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-2843AC\"></sup> on top of the food offerings presented to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>. It is a sin offering.",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>In this way the priest will make atonement<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-2844AD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AD&quot;&gt;AD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-2844AD\"></sup> for them for any of these sins they have committed, and they will be forgiven. The rest of the offering will belong to the priest,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-2844AE&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AE&quot;&gt;AE&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-2844AE\"></sup> as in the case of the grain offering.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-2844AF&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AF&quot;&gt;AF&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-2844AF\"></sup>’”",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>The <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> said to Moses:",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>“When anyone is unfaithful to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> by sinning unintentionally<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-2846AG&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AG&quot;&gt;AG&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-2846AG\"></sup> in regard to any of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>’s holy things, they are to bring to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> as a penalty<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-2846AH&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AH&quot;&gt;AH&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-2846AH\"></sup> a ram<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-2846AI&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AI&quot;&gt;AI&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-2846AI\"></sup> from the flock, one without defect and of the proper value in silver, according to the sanctuary shekel.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-2846AJ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AJ&quot;&gt;AJ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-2846AJ\"></sup> It is a guilt offering.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-2846AK&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AK&quot;&gt;AK&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-2846AK\"></sup>",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>They must make restitution<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-2847AL&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AL&quot;&gt;AL&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-2847AL\"></sup> for what they have failed to do in regard to the holy things, pay an additional penalty of a fifth of its value<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-2847AM&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AM&quot;&gt;AM&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-2847AM\"></sup> and give it all to the priest. The priest will make atonement for them with the ram as a guilt offering, and they will be forgiven.",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>“If anyone sins and does what is forbidden in any of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>’s commands, even though they do not know it,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-2848AN&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AN&quot;&gt;AN&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-2848AN\"></sup> they are guilty and will be held responsible.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-2848AO&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AO&quot;&gt;AO&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-2848AO\"></sup>",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>They are to bring to the priest as a guilt offering<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-2849AP&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AP&quot;&gt;AP&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-2849AP\"></sup> a ram from the flock, one without defect and of the proper value. In this way the priest will make atonement for them for the wrong they have committed unintentionally, and they will be forgiven.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-2849AQ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AQ&quot;&gt;AQ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-2849AQ\"></sup>",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>It is a guilt offering; they have been guilty of wrongdoing against the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-2850AR&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AR&quot;&gt;AR&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-2850AR\"></sup>"
		},
		"6": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">6 </span>The <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> said to Moses:",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>“If anyone sins and is unfaithful to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-2852A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-2852A\"></sup> by deceiving a neighbor<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-2852B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-2852B\"></sup> about something entrusted to them or left in their care<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-2852C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-2852C\"></sup> or about something stolen, or if they cheat<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-2852D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-2852D\"></sup> their neighbor,",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>or if they find lost property and lie about it,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-2853E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-2853E\"></sup> or if they swear falsely<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-2853F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-2853F\"></sup> about any such sin that people may commit—",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>when they sin in any of these ways and realize their guilt, they must return<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-2854G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-2854G\"></sup> what they have stolen or taken by extortion, or what was entrusted to them, or the lost property they found,",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>or whatever it was they swore falsely about. They must make restitution<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-2855H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-2855H\"></sup> in full, add a fifth of the value to it and give it all to the owner on the day they present their guilt offering.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-2855I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-2855I\"></sup>",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>And as a penalty they must bring to the priest, that is, to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, their guilt offering,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-2856J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-2856J\"></sup> a ram from the flock, one without defect and of the proper value.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-2856K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-2856K\"></sup>",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>In this way the priest will make atonement<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-2857L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-2857L\"></sup> for them before the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, and they will be forgiven for any of the things they did that made them guilty.”",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>The <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> said to Moses:",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>“Give Aaron and his sons this command: ‘These are the regulations for the burnt offering<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-2859M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-2859M\"></sup>: The burnt offering is to remain on the altar hearth throughout the night, till morning, and the fire must be kept burning on the altar.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-2859N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-2859N\"></sup>",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>The priest shall then put on his linen clothes,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-2860O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-2860O\"></sup> with linen undergarments next to his body,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-2860P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-2860P\"></sup> and shall remove the ashes<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-2860Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-2860Q\"></sup> of the burnt offering that the fire has consumed on the altar and place them beside the altar.",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>Then he is to take off these clothes and put on others, and carry the ashes outside the camp to a place that is ceremonially clean.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-2861R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-2861R\"></sup>",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>The fire on the altar must be kept burning; it must not go out. Every morning the priest is to add firewood<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-2862S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-2862S\"></sup> and arrange the burnt offering on the fire and burn the fat<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-2862T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-2862T\"></sup> of the fellowship offerings<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-2862U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-2862U\"></sup> on it.",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>The fire must be kept burning on the altar continuously; it must not go out.",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>“‘These are the regulations for the grain offering:<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-2864V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-2864V\"></sup> Aaron’s sons are to bring it before the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, in front of the altar.",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>The priest is to take a handful of the finest flour and some olive oil, together with all the incense<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-2865W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-2865W\"></sup> on the grain offering,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-2865X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-2865X\"></sup> and burn the memorial portion<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-2865Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-2865Y\"></sup> on the altar as an aroma pleasing to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>Aaron and his sons<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-2866Z&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Z&quot;&gt;Z&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-2866Z\"></sup> shall eat the rest<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-2866AA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AA&quot;&gt;AA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-2866AA\"></sup> of it, but it is to be eaten without yeast<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-2866AB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AB&quot;&gt;AB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-2866AB\"></sup> in the sanctuary area;<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-2866AC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AC&quot;&gt;AC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-2866AC\"></sup> they are to eat it in the courtyard<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-2866AD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AD&quot;&gt;AD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-2866AD\"></sup> of the tent of meeting.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-2866AE&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AE&quot;&gt;AE&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-2866AE\"></sup>",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>It must not be baked with yeast; I have given it as their share<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-2867AF&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AF&quot;&gt;AF&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-2867AF\"></sup> of the food offerings presented to me.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-2867AG&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AG&quot;&gt;AG&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-2867AG\"></sup> Like the sin offering and the guilt offering, it is most holy.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-2867AH&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AH&quot;&gt;AH&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-2867AH\"></sup>",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>Any male descendant of Aaron may eat it.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-2868AI&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AI&quot;&gt;AI&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-2868AI\"></sup> For all generations to come<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-2868AJ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AJ&quot;&gt;AJ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-2868AJ\"></sup> it is his perpetual share<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-2868AK&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AK&quot;&gt;AK&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-2868AK\"></sup> of the food offerings presented to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>. Whatever touches them will become holy.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-2868AL&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AL&quot;&gt;AL&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-2868AL\"></sup>’”",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>The <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> also said to Moses,",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>“This is the offering Aaron and his sons are to bring to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> on the day he is anointed:<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-2870AM&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AM&quot;&gt;AM&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-2870AM\"></sup> a tenth of an ephah<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-2870AN&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AN&quot;&gt;AN&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-2870AN\"></sup> of the finest flour<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-2870AO&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AO&quot;&gt;AO&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-2870AO\"></sup> as a regular grain offering,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-2870AP&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AP&quot;&gt;AP&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-2870AP\"></sup> half of it in the morning and half in the evening.",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>It must be prepared with oil on a griddle;<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-2871AQ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AQ&quot;&gt;AQ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-2871AQ\"></sup> bring it well-mixed and present the grain offering broken in pieces as an aroma pleasing to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>The son who is to succeed him as anointed priest<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-2872AR&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AR&quot;&gt;AR&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-2872AR\"></sup> shall prepare it. It is the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>’s perpetual share and is to be burned completely.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-2872AS&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AS&quot;&gt;AS&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-2872AS\"></sup>",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>Every grain offering of a priest shall be burned completely; it must not be eaten.”",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup>The <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> said to Moses,",
			"25": "<sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup>“Say to Aaron and his sons: ‘These are the regulations for the sin offering:<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-2875AT&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AT&quot;&gt;AT&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-2875AT\"></sup> The sin offering is to be slaughtered before the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-2875AU&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AU&quot;&gt;AU&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-2875AU\"></sup> in the place<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-2875AV&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AV&quot;&gt;AV&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-2875AV\"></sup> the burnt offering is slaughtered; it is most holy.",
			"26": "<sup class=\"versenum\">26 </sup>The priest who offers it shall eat it; it is to be eaten in the sanctuary area,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-2876AW&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AW&quot;&gt;AW&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-2876AW\"></sup> in the courtyard<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-2876AX&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AX&quot;&gt;AX&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-2876AX\"></sup> of the tent of meeting.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-2876AY&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AY&quot;&gt;AY&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-2876AY\"></sup>",
			"27": "<sup class=\"versenum\">27 </sup>Whatever touches any of the flesh will become holy,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-2877AZ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AZ&quot;&gt;AZ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-2877AZ\"></sup> and if any of the blood is spattered on a garment, you must wash it in the sanctuary area.",
			"28": "<sup class=\"versenum\">28 </sup>The clay pot<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-2878BA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BA&quot;&gt;BA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-2878BA\"></sup> the meat is cooked in must be broken; but if it is cooked in a bronze pot, the pot is to be scoured and rinsed with water.",
			"29": "<sup class=\"versenum\">29 </sup>Any male in a priest’s family may eat it;<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-2879BB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BB&quot;&gt;BB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-2879BB\"></sup> it is most holy.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-2879BC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BC&quot;&gt;BC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-2879BC\"></sup>",
			"30": "<sup class=\"versenum\">30 </sup>But any sin offering whose blood is brought into the tent of meeting to make atonement<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-2880BD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BD&quot;&gt;BD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-2880BD\"></sup> in the Holy Place<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-2880BE&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BE&quot;&gt;BE&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-2880BE\"></sup> must not be eaten; it must be burned up.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-2880BF&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BF&quot;&gt;BF&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-2880BF\"></sup>"
		},
		"7": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">7 </span>“‘These are the regulations for the guilt offering,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-2881A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-2881A\"></sup> which is most holy:",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>The guilt offering is to be slaughtered in the place where the burnt offering is slaughtered, and its blood is to be splashed against the sides of the altar.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>All its fat<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-2883B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-2883B\"></sup> shall be offered: the fat tail and the fat that covers the internal organs,",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>both kidneys with the fat on them near the loins, and the long lobe of the liver, which is to be removed with the kidneys.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-2884C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-2884C\"></sup>",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>The priest shall burn them on the altar<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-2885D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-2885D\"></sup> as a food offering presented to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>. It is a guilt offering.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>Any male in a priest’s family may eat it,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-2886E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-2886E\"></sup> but it must be eaten in the sanctuary area; it is most holy.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-2886F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-2886F\"></sup>",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>“‘The same law applies to both the sin offering<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-2887G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-2887G\"></sup> and the guilt offering:<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-2887H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-2887H\"></sup> They belong to the priest<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-2887I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-2887I\"></sup> who makes atonement with them.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-2887J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-2887J\"></sup>",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>The priest who offers a burnt offering for anyone may keep its hide<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-2888K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-2888K\"></sup> for himself.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>Every grain offering baked in an oven<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-2889L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-2889L\"></sup> or cooked in a pan<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-2889M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-2889M\"></sup> or on a griddle<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-2889N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-2889N\"></sup> belongs to the priest who offers it,",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>and every grain offering, whether mixed with olive oil or dry, belongs equally to all the sons of Aaron.",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>“‘These are the regulations for the fellowship offering anyone may present to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>:",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>“‘If they offer it as an expression of thankfulness, then along with this thank offering<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-2892O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-2892O\"></sup> they are to offer thick loaves<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-2892P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-2892P\"></sup> made without yeast<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-2892Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-2892Q\"></sup> and with olive oil mixed in, thin loaves<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-2892R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-2892R\"></sup> made without yeast and brushed with oil,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-2892S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-2892S\"></sup> and thick loaves of the finest flour well-kneaded and with oil mixed in.",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>Along with their fellowship offering of thanksgiving<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-2893T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-2893T\"></sup> they are to present an offering with thick loaves of bread made with yeast.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-2893U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-2893U\"></sup>",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>They are to bring one of each kind as an offering, a contribution to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>; it belongs to the priest who splashes the blood of the fellowship offering against the altar.",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>The meat of their fellowship offering of thanksgiving must be eaten on the day it is offered; they must leave none of it till morning.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-2895V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-2895V\"></sup>",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>“‘If, however, their offering is the result of a vow<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-2896W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-2896W\"></sup> or is a freewill offering,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-2896X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-2896X\"></sup> the sacrifice shall be eaten on the day they offer it, but anything left over may be eaten on the next day.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-2896Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-2896Y\"></sup>",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>Any meat of the sacrifice left over till the third day must be burned up.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-2897Z&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Z&quot;&gt;Z&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-2897Z\"></sup>",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>If any meat of the fellowship offering<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-2898AA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AA&quot;&gt;AA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-2898AA\"></sup> is eaten on the third day, the one who offered it will not be accepted.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-2898AB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AB&quot;&gt;AB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-2898AB\"></sup> It will not be reckoned<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-2898AC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AC&quot;&gt;AC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-2898AC\"></sup> to their credit, for it has become impure; the person who eats any of it will be held responsible.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-2898AD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AD&quot;&gt;AD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-2898AD\"></sup>",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>“‘Meat that touches anything ceremonially unclean must not be eaten; it must be burned up. As for other meat, anyone ceremonially clean may eat it.",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>But if anyone who is unclean<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-2900AE&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AE&quot;&gt;AE&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-2900AE\"></sup> eats any meat of the fellowship offering belonging to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, they must be cut off from their people.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-2900AF&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AF&quot;&gt;AF&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-2900AF\"></sup>",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>Anyone who touches something unclean<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-2901AG&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AG&quot;&gt;AG&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-2901AG\"></sup>—whether human uncleanness or an unclean animal or any unclean creature that moves along the ground—and then eats any of the meat of the fellowship offering belonging to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> must be cut off from their people.’”",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>The <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> said to Moses,",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>“Say to the Israelites: ‘Do not eat any of the fat of cattle, sheep or goats.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-2903AH&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AH&quot;&gt;AH&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-2903AH\"></sup>",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup>The fat of an animal found dead or torn by wild animals<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-2904AI&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AI&quot;&gt;AI&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-2904AI\"></sup> may be used for any other purpose, but you must not eat it.",
			"25": "<sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup>Anyone who eats the fat of an animal from which a food offering may be presented to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> must be cut off from their people.",
			"26": "<sup class=\"versenum\">26 </sup>And wherever you live, you must not eat the blood<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-2906AJ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AJ&quot;&gt;AJ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-2906AJ\"></sup> of any bird or animal.",
			"27": "<sup class=\"versenum\">27 </sup>Anyone who eats blood<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-2907AK&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AK&quot;&gt;AK&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-2907AK\"></sup> must be cut off from their people.’”",
			"28": "<sup class=\"versenum\">28 </sup>The <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> said to Moses,",
			"29": "<sup class=\"versenum\">29 </sup>“Say to the Israelites: ‘Anyone who brings a fellowship offering to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> is to bring part of it as their sacrifice to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.",
			"30": "<sup class=\"versenum\">30 </sup>With their own hands they are to present the food offering to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>; they are to bring the fat, together with the breast, and wave the breast before the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> as a wave offering.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-2910AL&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AL&quot;&gt;AL&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-2910AL\"></sup>",
			"31": "<sup class=\"versenum\">31 </sup>The priest shall burn the fat on the altar,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-2911AM&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AM&quot;&gt;AM&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-2911AM\"></sup> but the breast belongs to Aaron and his sons.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-2911AN&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AN&quot;&gt;AN&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-2911AN\"></sup>",
			"32": "<sup class=\"versenum\">32 </sup>You are to give the right thigh of your fellowship offerings to the priest as a contribution.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-2912AO&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AO&quot;&gt;AO&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-2912AO\"></sup>",
			"33": "<sup class=\"versenum\">33 </sup>The son of Aaron who offers the blood and the fat of the fellowship offering shall have the right thigh as his share.",
			"34": "<sup class=\"versenum\">34 </sup>From the fellowship offerings of the Israelites, I have taken the breast that is waved and the thigh<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-2914AP&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AP&quot;&gt;AP&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-2914AP\"></sup> that is presented and have given them to Aaron the priest and his sons<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-2914AQ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AQ&quot;&gt;AQ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-2914AQ\"></sup> as their perpetual share from the Israelites.’”",
			"35": "<sup class=\"versenum\">35 </sup>This is the portion of the food offerings presented to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> that were allotted to Aaron and his sons on the day they were presented to serve the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> as priests.",
			"36": "<sup class=\"versenum\">36 </sup>On the day they were anointed,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-2916AR&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AR&quot;&gt;AR&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-2916AR\"></sup> the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> commanded that the Israelites give this to them as their perpetual share for the generations to come.",
			"37": "<sup class=\"versenum\">37 </sup>These, then, are the regulations for the burnt offering,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-2917AS&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AS&quot;&gt;AS&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-2917AS\"></sup> the grain offering,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-2917AT&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AT&quot;&gt;AT&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-2917AT\"></sup> the sin offering, the guilt offering, the ordination offering<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-2917AU&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AU&quot;&gt;AU&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-2917AU\"></sup> and the fellowship offering,",
			"38": "<sup class=\"versenum\">38 </sup>which the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> gave Moses<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-2918AV&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AV&quot;&gt;AV&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-2918AV\"></sup> at Mount Sinai<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-2918AW&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AW&quot;&gt;AW&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-2918AW\"></sup> in the Desert of Sinai on the day he commanded the Israelites to bring their offerings to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-2918AX&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AX&quot;&gt;AX&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-2918AX\"></sup>"
		},
		"8": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">8 </span>The <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> said to Moses,",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>“Bring Aaron and his sons,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-2920B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-2920B\"></sup> their garments,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-2920C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-2920C\"></sup> the anointing oil,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-2920D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-2920D\"></sup> the bull for the sin offering,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-2920E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-2920E\"></sup> the two rams<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-2920F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-2920F\"></sup> and the basket containing bread made without yeast,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-2920G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-2920G\"></sup>",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>and gather the entire assembly<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-2921H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-2921H\"></sup> at the entrance to the tent of meeting.”",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>Moses did as the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> commanded him, and the assembly gathered at the entrance to the tent of meeting.",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>Moses said to the assembly, “This is what the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> has commanded to be done.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-2923I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-2923I\"></sup>”",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>Then Moses brought Aaron and his sons forward and washed them with water.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-2924J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-2924J\"></sup>",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>He put the tunic on Aaron, tied the sash around him, clothed him with the robe and put the ephod on him. He also fastened the ephod with a decorative waistband, which he tied around him.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-2925K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-2925K\"></sup>",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>He placed the breastpiece<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-2926L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-2926L\"></sup> on him and put the Urim and Thummim<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-2926M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-2926M\"></sup> in the breastpiece.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>Then he placed the turban<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-2927N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-2927N\"></sup> on Aaron’s head and set the gold plate, the sacred emblem,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-2927O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-2927O\"></sup> on the front of it, as the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> commanded Moses.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-2927P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-2927P\"></sup>",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>Then Moses took the anointing oil<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-2928Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-2928Q\"></sup> and anointed<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-2928R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-2928R\"></sup> the tabernacle<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-2928S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-2928S\"></sup> and everything in it, and so consecrated them.",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>He sprinkled some of the oil on the altar seven times, anointing the altar and all its utensils and the basin with its stand, to consecrate them.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-2929T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-2929T\"></sup>",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>He poured some of the anointing oil on Aaron’s head and anointed<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-2930U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-2930U\"></sup> him to consecrate him.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-2930V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-2930V\"></sup>",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>Then he brought Aaron’s sons<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-2931W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-2931W\"></sup> forward, put tunics<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-2931X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-2931X\"></sup> on them, tied sashes around them and fastened caps on them, as the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> commanded Moses.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-2931Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-2931Y\"></sup>",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>He then presented the bull<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-2932Z&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Z&quot;&gt;Z&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-2932Z\"></sup> for the sin offering,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-2932AA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AA&quot;&gt;AA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-2932AA\"></sup> and Aaron and his sons laid their hands on its head.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-2932AB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AB&quot;&gt;AB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-2932AB\"></sup>",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>Moses slaughtered the bull and took some of the blood,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-2933AC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AC&quot;&gt;AC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-2933AC\"></sup> and with his finger he put it on all the horns of the altar<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-2933AD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AD&quot;&gt;AD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-2933AD\"></sup> to purify the altar.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-2933AE&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AE&quot;&gt;AE&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-2933AE\"></sup> He poured out the rest of the blood at the base of the altar. So he consecrated it to make atonement for it.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-2933AF&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AF&quot;&gt;AF&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-2933AF\"></sup>",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>Moses also took all the fat around the internal organs, the long lobe of the liver, and both kidneys and their fat, and burned it on the altar.",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>But the bull with its hide and its flesh and its intestines<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-2935AG&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AG&quot;&gt;AG&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-2935AG\"></sup> he burned up outside the camp,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-2935AH&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AH&quot;&gt;AH&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-2935AH\"></sup> as the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> commanded Moses.",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>He then presented the ram<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-2936AI&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AI&quot;&gt;AI&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-2936AI\"></sup> for the burnt offering, and Aaron and his sons laid their hands on its head.",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>Then Moses slaughtered the ram and splashed the blood against the sides of the altar.",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>He cut the ram into pieces and burned the head, the pieces and the fat.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-2938AJ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AJ&quot;&gt;AJ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-2938AJ\"></sup>",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>He washed the internal organs and the legs with water and burned the whole ram on the altar. It was a burnt offering, a pleasing aroma, a food offering presented to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, as the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> commanded Moses.",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>He then presented the other ram, the ram for the ordination,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-2940AK&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AK&quot;&gt;AK&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-2940AK\"></sup> and Aaron and his sons laid their hands on its head.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-2940AL&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AL&quot;&gt;AL&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-2940AL\"></sup>",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>Moses slaughtered the ram and took some of its blood and put it on the lobe of Aaron’s right ear, on the thumb of his right hand and on the big toe of his right foot.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-2941AM&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AM&quot;&gt;AM&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-2941AM\"></sup>",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup>Moses also brought Aaron’s sons forward and put some of the blood on the lobes of their right ears, on the thumbs of their right hands and on the big toes of their right feet. Then he splashed blood against the sides of the altar.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-2942AN&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AN&quot;&gt;AN&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-2942AN\"></sup>",
			"25": "<sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup>After that, he took the fat<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-2943AO&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AO&quot;&gt;AO&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-2943AO\"></sup>, the fat tail, all the fat around the internal organs, the long lobe of the liver, both kidneys and their fat and the right thigh.",
			"26": "<sup class=\"versenum\">26 </sup>And from the basket of bread made without yeast, which was before the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, he took one thick loaf, one thick loaf with olive oil mixed in, and one thin loaf,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-2944AP&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AP&quot;&gt;AP&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-2944AP\"></sup> and he put these on the fat portions and on the right thigh.",
			"27": "<sup class=\"versenum\">27 </sup>He put all these in the hands of Aaron and his sons, and they waved them before the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-2945AQ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AQ&quot;&gt;AQ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-2945AQ\"></sup> as a wave offering.",
			"28": "<sup class=\"versenum\">28 </sup>Then Moses took them from their hands and burned them on the altar on top of the burnt offering as an ordination offering, a pleasing aroma, a food offering presented to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.",
			"29": "<sup class=\"versenum\">29 </sup>Moses also took the breast, which was his share of the ordination ram,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-2947AR&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AR&quot;&gt;AR&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-2947AR\"></sup> and waved it before the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> as a wave offering, as the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> commanded Moses.",
			"30": "<sup class=\"versenum\">30 </sup>Then Moses<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-2948AS&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AS&quot;&gt;AS&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-2948AS\"></sup> took some of the anointing oil and some of the blood from the altar and sprinkled them on Aaron and his garments<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-2948AT&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AT&quot;&gt;AT&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-2948AT\"></sup> and on his sons and their garments. So he consecrated<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-2948AU&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AU&quot;&gt;AU&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-2948AU\"></sup> Aaron and his garments and his sons and their garments.",
			"31": "<sup class=\"versenum\">31 </sup>Moses then said to Aaron and his sons, “Cook the meat at the entrance to the tent of meeting<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-2949AV&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AV&quot;&gt;AV&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-2949AV\"></sup> and eat it there with the bread from the basket of ordination offerings, as I was commanded: ‘Aaron and his sons are to eat it.’",
			"32": "<sup class=\"versenum\">32 </sup>Then burn up the rest of the meat and the bread.",
			"33": "<sup class=\"versenum\">33 </sup>Do not leave the entrance to the tent of meeting for seven days, until the days of your ordination are completed, for your ordination will last seven days.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-2951AW&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AW&quot;&gt;AW&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-2951AW\"></sup>",
			"34": "<sup class=\"versenum\">34 </sup>What has been done today was commanded by the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-2952AX&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AX&quot;&gt;AX&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-2952AX\"></sup> to make atonement for you.",
			"35": "<sup class=\"versenum\">35 </sup>You must stay at the entrance to the tent of meeting day and night for seven days and do what the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> requires,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-2953AY&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AY&quot;&gt;AY&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-2953AY\"></sup> so you will not die; for that is what I have been commanded.”",
			"36": "<sup class=\"versenum\">36 </sup>So Aaron and his sons did everything the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> commanded through Moses."
		},
		"9": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">9 </span>On the eighth day<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-2955A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-2955A\"></sup> Moses summoned Aaron and his sons and the elders<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-2955B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-2955B\"></sup> of Israel.",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>He said to Aaron, “Take a bull calf for your sin offering and a ram for your burnt offering, both without defect, and present them before the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>Then say to the Israelites: ‘Take a male goat<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-2957C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-2957C\"></sup> for a sin offering,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-2957D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-2957D\"></sup> a calf<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-2957E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-2957E\"></sup> and a lamb<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-2957F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-2957F\"></sup>—both a year old and without defect—for a burnt offering,",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>and an ox<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-2958G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-2958G\"></sup> and a ram for a fellowship offering<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-2958H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-2958H\"></sup> to sacrifice before the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, together with a grain offering mixed with olive oil. For today the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> will appear to you.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-2958I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-2958I\"></sup>’”",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>They took the things Moses commanded to the front of the tent of meeting, and the entire assembly came near and stood before the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>Then Moses said, “This is what the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> has commanded you to do, so that the glory of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-2960J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-2960J\"></sup> may appear to you.”",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>Moses said to Aaron, “Come to the altar and sacrifice your sin offering and your burnt offering and make atonement for yourself and the people;<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-2961K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-2961K\"></sup> sacrifice the offering that is for the people and make atonement for them, as the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> has commanded.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-2961L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-2961L\"></sup>”",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>So Aaron came to the altar and slaughtered the calf as a sin offering<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-2962M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-2962M\"></sup> for himself.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>His sons brought the blood to him,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-2963N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-2963N\"></sup> and he dipped his finger into the blood and put it on the horns of the altar; the rest of the blood he poured out at the base of the altar.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-2963O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-2963O\"></sup>",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>On the altar he burned the fat, the kidneys and the long lobe of the liver from the sin offering, as the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> commanded Moses;",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>the flesh and the hide<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-2965P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-2965P\"></sup> he burned up outside the camp.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-2965Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-2965Q\"></sup>",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>Then he slaughtered the burnt offering.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-2966R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-2966R\"></sup> His sons handed him the blood,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-2966S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-2966S\"></sup> and he splashed it against the sides of the altar.",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>They handed him the burnt offering piece by piece, including the head, and he burned them on the altar.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-2967T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-2967T\"></sup>",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>He washed the internal organs and the legs and burned them on top of the burnt offering on the altar.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-2968U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-2968U\"></sup>",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>Aaron then brought the offering that was for the people.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-2969V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-2969V\"></sup> He took the goat for the people’s sin offering and slaughtered it and offered it for a sin offering as he did with the first one.",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>He brought the burnt offering and offered it in the prescribed way.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-2970W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-2970W\"></sup>",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>He also brought the grain offering, took a handful of it and burned it on the altar in addition to the morning’s burnt offering.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-2971X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-2971X\"></sup>",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>He slaughtered the ox and the ram as the fellowship offering for the people.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-2972Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-2972Y\"></sup> His sons handed him the blood, and he splashed it against the sides of the altar.",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>But the fat portions of the ox and the ram—the fat tail, the layer of fat, the kidneys and the long lobe of the liver—",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>these they laid on the breasts, and then Aaron burned the fat on the altar.",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>Aaron waved the breasts and the right thigh before the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> as a wave offering,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-2975Z&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Z&quot;&gt;Z&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-2975Z\"></sup> as Moses commanded.",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>Then Aaron lifted his hands toward the people and blessed them.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-2976AA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AA&quot;&gt;AA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-2976AA\"></sup> And having sacrificed the sin offering, the burnt offering and the fellowship offering, he stepped down.",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>Moses and Aaron then went into the tent of meeting.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-2977AB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AB&quot;&gt;AB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-2977AB\"></sup> When they came out, they blessed the people; and the glory of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-2977AC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AC&quot;&gt;AC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-2977AC\"></sup> appeared to all the people.",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup>Fire<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-2978AD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AD&quot;&gt;AD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-2978AD\"></sup> came out from the presence of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> and consumed the burnt offering and the fat portions on the altar. And when all the people saw it, they shouted for joy and fell facedown.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-2978AE&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AE&quot;&gt;AE&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-2978AE\"></sup>"
		},
		"10": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">10 </span>Aaron’s sons Nadab and Abihu<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-2979A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-2979A\"></sup> took their censers,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-2979B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-2979B\"></sup> put fire in them<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-2979C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-2979C\"></sup> and added incense;<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-2979D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-2979D\"></sup> and they offered unauthorized fire before the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-2979E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-2979E\"></sup> contrary to his command.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-2979F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-2979F\"></sup>",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>So fire came out<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-2980G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-2980G\"></sup> from the presence of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> and consumed them,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-2980H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-2980H\"></sup> and they died before the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-2980I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-2980I\"></sup>",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>Moses then said to Aaron, “This is what the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> spoke of when he said:“‘Among those who approach me<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-2981J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-2981J\"></sup>I will be proved holy;<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-2981K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-2981K\"></sup>in the sight of all the peopleI will be honored.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-2981L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-2981L\"></sup>’”Aaron remained silent.",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>Moses summoned Mishael and Elzaphan,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-2982M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-2982M\"></sup> sons of Aaron’s uncle Uzziel,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-2982N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-2982N\"></sup> and said to them, “Come here; carry your cousins outside the camp,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-2982O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-2982O\"></sup> away from the front of the sanctuary.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-2982P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-2982P\"></sup>”",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>So they came and carried them, still in their tunics,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-2983Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-2983Q\"></sup> outside the camp, as Moses ordered.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>Then Moses said to Aaron and his sons Eleazar and Ithamar,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-2984R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-2984R\"></sup> “Do not let your hair become unkempt<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-2984S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-2984S\"></sup> and do not tear your clothes,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-2984T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-2984T\"></sup> or you will die and the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> will be angry with the whole community.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-2984U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-2984U\"></sup> But your relatives, all the Israelites, may mourn<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-2984V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-2984V\"></sup> for those the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> has destroyed by fire.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>Do not leave the entrance to the tent of meeting<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-2985W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-2985W\"></sup> or you will die, because the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>’s anointing oil<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-2985X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-2985X\"></sup> is on you.” So they did as Moses said.",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>Then the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> said to Aaron,",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>“You and your sons are not to drink wine<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-2987Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-2987Y\"></sup> or other fermented drink<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-2987Z&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Z&quot;&gt;Z&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-2987Z\"></sup> whenever you go into the tent of meeting, or you will die. This is a lasting ordinance<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-2987AA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AA&quot;&gt;AA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-2987AA\"></sup> for the generations to come,",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>so that you can distinguish between the holy and the common, between the unclean and the clean,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-2988AB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AB&quot;&gt;AB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-2988AB\"></sup>",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>and so you can teach<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-2989AC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AC&quot;&gt;AC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-2989AC\"></sup> the Israelites all the decrees the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> has given them through Moses.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-2989AD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AD&quot;&gt;AD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-2989AD\"></sup>”",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>Moses said to Aaron and his remaining sons, Eleazar and Ithamar, “Take the grain offering<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-2990AE&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AE&quot;&gt;AE&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-2990AE\"></sup> left over from the food offerings prepared without yeast and presented to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> and eat it beside the altar,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-2990AF&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AF&quot;&gt;AF&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-2990AF\"></sup> for it is most holy.",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>Eat it in the sanctuary area,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-2991AG&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AG&quot;&gt;AG&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-2991AG\"></sup> because it is your share and your sons’ share of the food offerings presented to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>; for so I have been commanded.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-2991AH&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AH&quot;&gt;AH&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-2991AH\"></sup>",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>But you and your sons and your daughters may eat the breast<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-2992AI&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AI&quot;&gt;AI&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-2992AI\"></sup> that was waved and the thigh that was presented. Eat them in a ceremonially clean place;<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-2992AJ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AJ&quot;&gt;AJ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-2992AJ\"></sup> they have been given to you and your children as your share of the Israelites’ fellowship offerings.",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>The thigh<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-2993AK&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AK&quot;&gt;AK&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-2993AK\"></sup> that was presented and the breast that was waved must be brought with the fat portions of the food offerings, to be waved before the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> as a wave offering.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-2993AL&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AL&quot;&gt;AL&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-2993AL\"></sup> This will be the perpetual share for you and your children, as the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> has commanded.”",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>When Moses inquired about the goat of the sin offering<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-2994AM&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AM&quot;&gt;AM&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-2994AM\"></sup> and found that it had been burned up, he was angry with Eleazar and Ithamar, Aaron’s remaining sons, and asked,",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>“Why didn’t you eat the sin offering<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-2995AN&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AN&quot;&gt;AN&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-2995AN\"></sup> in the sanctuary area? It is most holy; it was given to you to take away the guilt<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-2995AO&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AO&quot;&gt;AO&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-2995AO\"></sup> of the community by making atonement for them before the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>Since its blood was not taken into the Holy Place,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-2996AP&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AP&quot;&gt;AP&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-2996AP\"></sup> you should have eaten the goat in the sanctuary area, as I commanded.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-2996AQ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AQ&quot;&gt;AQ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-2996AQ\"></sup>”",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>Aaron replied to Moses, “Today they sacrificed their sin offering and their burnt offering<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-2997AR&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AR&quot;&gt;AR&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-2997AR\"></sup> before the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, but such things as this have happened to me. Would the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> have been pleased if I had eaten the sin offering today?”",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>When Moses heard this, he was satisfied."
		},
		"11": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">11 </span>The <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> said to Moses and Aaron,",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>“Say to the Israelites: ‘Of all the animals that live on land, these are the ones you may eat:<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3000B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3000B\"></sup>",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>You may eat any animal that has a divided hoof and that chews the cud.",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>“‘There are some that only chew the cud or only have a divided hoof, but you must not eat them.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3002C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3002C\"></sup> The camel, though it chews the cud, does not have a divided hoof; it is ceremonially unclean for you.",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>The hyrax, though it chews the cud, does not have a divided hoof; it is unclean for you.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>The rabbit, though it chews the cud, does not have a divided hoof; it is unclean for you.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>And the pig,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3005D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3005D\"></sup> though it has a divided hoof, does not chew the cud; it is unclean for you.",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>You must not eat their meat or touch their carcasses; they are unclean for you.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3006E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3006E\"></sup>",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>“‘Of all the creatures living in the water of the seas and the streams you may eat any that have fins and scales.",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>But all creatures in the seas or streams that do not have fins and scales—whether among all the swarming things or among all the other living creatures in the water—you are to regard as unclean.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3008F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3008F\"></sup>",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>And since you are to regard them as unclean, you must not eat their meat; you must regard their carcasses as unclean.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3009G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3009G\"></sup>",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>Anything living in the water that does not have fins and scales is to be regarded as unclean by you.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3010H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3010H\"></sup>",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>“‘These are the birds you are to regard as unclean and not eat because they are unclean: the eagle, the vulture, the black vulture,",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>the red kite, any kind<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3012I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3012I\"></sup> of black kite,",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>any kind of raven,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3013J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3013J\"></sup>",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>the horned owl, the screech owl, the gull, any kind of hawk,",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>the little owl, the cormorant, the great owl,",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>the white owl,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3016K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3016K\"></sup> the desert owl, the osprey,",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>the stork,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3017L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3017L\"></sup> any kind<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3017M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3017M\"></sup> of heron, the hoopoe and the bat.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3017N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3017N\"></sup>",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>“‘All flying insects that walk on all fours are to be regarded as unclean by you.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3018O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3018O\"></sup>",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>There are, however, some flying insects that walk on all fours that you may eat: those that have jointed legs for hopping on the ground.",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>Of these you may eat any kind of locust,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3020P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3020P\"></sup> katydid, cricket or grasshopper.",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>But all other flying insects that have four legs you are to regard as unclean.",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup>“‘You will make yourselves unclean by these;<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3022Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3022Q\"></sup> whoever touches their carcasses will be unclean till evening.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3022R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3022R\"></sup>",
			"25": "<sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup>Whoever picks up one of their carcasses must wash their clothes,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3023S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3023S\"></sup> and they will be unclean till evening.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3023T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3023T\"></sup>",
			"26": "<sup class=\"versenum\">26 </sup>“‘Every animal that does not have a divided hoof or that does not chew the cud is unclean for you; whoever touches the carcass of any of them will be unclean.",
			"27": "<sup class=\"versenum\">27 </sup>Of all the animals that walk on all fours, those that walk on their paws are unclean for you; whoever touches their carcasses will be unclean till evening.",
			"28": "<sup class=\"versenum\">28 </sup>Anyone who picks up their carcasses must wash their clothes, and they will be unclean till evening.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3026U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3026U\"></sup> These animals are unclean for you.",
			"29": "<sup class=\"versenum\">29 </sup>“‘Of the animals that move along the ground, these are unclean for you:<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3027V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3027V\"></sup> the weasel, the rat,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3027W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3027W\"></sup> any kind of great lizard,",
			"30": "<sup class=\"versenum\">30 </sup>the gecko, the monitor lizard, the wall lizard, the skink and the chameleon.",
			"31": "<sup class=\"versenum\">31 </sup>Of all those that move along the ground, these are unclean for you. Whoever touches them when they are dead will be unclean till evening.",
			"32": "<sup class=\"versenum\">32 </sup>When one of them dies and falls on something, that article, whatever its use, will be unclean, whether it is made of wood, cloth, hide or sackcloth.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3030X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3030X\"></sup> Put it in water; it will be unclean till evening, and then it will be clean.",
			"33": "<sup class=\"versenum\">33 </sup>If one of them falls into a clay pot, everything in it will be unclean, and you must break the pot.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3031Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3031Y\"></sup>",
			"34": "<sup class=\"versenum\">34 </sup>Any food you are allowed to eat that has come into contact with water from any such pot is unclean, and any liquid that is drunk from such a pot is unclean.",
			"35": "<sup class=\"versenum\">35 </sup>Anything that one of their carcasses falls on becomes unclean; an oven or cooking pot must be broken up. They are unclean, and you are to regard them as unclean.",
			"36": "<sup class=\"versenum\">36 </sup>A spring, however, or a cistern for collecting water remains clean, but anyone who touches one of these carcasses is unclean.",
			"37": "<sup class=\"versenum\">37 </sup>If a carcass falls on any seeds that are to be planted, they remain clean.",
			"38": "<sup class=\"versenum\">38 </sup>But if water has been put on the seed and a carcass falls on it, it is unclean for you.",
			"39": "<sup class=\"versenum\">39 </sup>“‘If an animal that you are allowed to eat dies,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3037Z&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Z&quot;&gt;Z&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3037Z\"></sup> anyone who touches its carcass<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3037AA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AA&quot;&gt;AA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3037AA\"></sup> will be unclean till evening.",
			"40": "<sup class=\"versenum\">40 </sup>Anyone who eats some of its carcass<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3038AB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AB&quot;&gt;AB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3038AB\"></sup> must wash their clothes, and they will be unclean till evening.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3038AC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AC&quot;&gt;AC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3038AC\"></sup> Anyone who picks up the carcass must wash their clothes, and they will be unclean till evening.",
			"41": "<sup class=\"versenum\">41 </sup>“‘Every creature that moves along the ground is to be regarded as unclean; it is not to be eaten.",
			"42": "<sup class=\"versenum\">42 </sup>You are not to eat any creature that moves along the ground, whether it moves on its belly or walks on all fours or on many feet; it is unclean.",
			"43": "<sup class=\"versenum\">43 </sup>Do not defile yourselves by any of these creatures.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3041AD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AD&quot;&gt;AD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3041AD\"></sup> Do not make yourselves unclean by means of them or be made unclean by them.",
			"44": "<sup class=\"versenum\">44 </sup>I am the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God;<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3042AE&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AE&quot;&gt;AE&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3042AE\"></sup> consecrate yourselves<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3042AF&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AF&quot;&gt;AF&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3042AF\"></sup> and be holy,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3042AG&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AG&quot;&gt;AG&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3042AG\"></sup> because I am holy.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3042AH&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AH&quot;&gt;AH&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3042AH\"></sup> Do not make yourselves unclean by any creature that moves along the ground.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3042AI&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AI&quot;&gt;AI&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3042AI\"></sup>",
			"45": "<sup class=\"versenum\">45 </sup>I am the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, who brought you up out of Egypt<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3043AJ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AJ&quot;&gt;AJ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3043AJ\"></sup> to be your God;<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3043AK&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AK&quot;&gt;AK&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3043AK\"></sup> therefore be holy, because I am holy.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3043AL&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AL&quot;&gt;AL&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3043AL\"></sup>",
			"46": "<sup class=\"versenum\">46 </sup>“‘These are the regulations concerning animals, birds, every living thing that moves about in the water and every creature that moves along the ground.",
			"47": "<sup class=\"versenum\">47 </sup>You must distinguish between the unclean and the clean, between living creatures that may be eaten and those that may not be eaten.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3045AM&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AM&quot;&gt;AM&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3045AM\"></sup>’”"
		},
		"12": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">12 </span>The <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> said to Moses,",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>“Say to the Israelites: ‘A woman who becomes pregnant and gives birth to a son will be ceremonially unclean for seven days, just as she is unclean during her monthly period.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3047A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3047A\"></sup>",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>On the eighth day<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3048B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3048B\"></sup> the boy is to be circumcised.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3048C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3048C\"></sup>",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>Then the woman must wait thirty-three days to be purified from her bleeding. She must not touch anything sacred or go to the sanctuary until the days of her purification are over.",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>If she gives birth to a daughter, for two weeks the woman will be unclean, as during her period. Then she must wait sixty-six days to be purified from her bleeding.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>“‘When the days of her purification for a son or daughter are over,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3051D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3051D\"></sup> she is to bring to the priest at the entrance to the tent of meeting a year-old lamb<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3051E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3051E\"></sup> for a burnt offering and a young pigeon or a dove for a sin offering.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3051F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3051F\"></sup>",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>He shall offer them before the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> to make atonement for her, and then she will be ceremonially clean from her flow of blood.“‘These are the regulations for the woman who gives birth to a boy or a girl.",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>But if she cannot afford a lamb, she is to bring two doves or two young pigeons,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3053G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3053G\"></sup> one for a burnt offering and the other for a sin offering.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3053H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3053H\"></sup> In this way the priest will make atonement for her, and she will be clean.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3053I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3053I\"></sup>’”"
		},
		"13": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">13 </span>The <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> said to Moses and Aaron,",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>“When anyone has a swelling<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3055A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3055A\"></sup> or a rash or a shiny spot<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3055B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3055B\"></sup> on their skin that may be a defiling skin disease,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3055C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3055C\"></sup> they must be brought to Aaron the priest<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3055D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3055D\"></sup> or to one of his sons who is a priest.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>The priest is to examine the sore on the skin, and if the hair in the sore has turned white and the sore appears to be more than skin deep, it is a defiling skin disease. When the priest examines that person, he shall pronounce them ceremonially unclean.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3056E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3056E\"></sup>",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>If the shiny spot<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3057F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3057F\"></sup> on the skin is white but does not appear to be more than skin deep and the hair in it has not turned white, the priest is to isolate the affected person for seven days.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3057G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3057G\"></sup>",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>On the seventh day<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3058H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3058H\"></sup> the priest is to examine them,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3058I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3058I\"></sup> and if he sees that the sore is unchanged and has not spread in the skin, he is to isolate them for another seven days.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>On the seventh day the priest is to examine them again, and if the sore has faded and has not spread in the skin, the priest shall pronounce them clean;<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3059J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3059J\"></sup> it is only a rash. They must wash their clothes,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3059K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3059K\"></sup> and they will be clean.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3059L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3059L\"></sup>",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>But if the rash does spread in their skin after they have shown themselves to the priest to be pronounced clean, they must appear before the priest again.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3060M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3060M\"></sup>",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>The priest is to examine that person, and if the rash has spread in the skin, he shall pronounce them unclean; it is a defiling skin disease.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>“When anyone has a defiling skin disease, they must be brought to the priest.",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>The priest is to examine them, and if there is a white swelling in the skin that has turned the hair white and if there is raw flesh in the swelling,",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>it is a chronic skin disease<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3064N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3064N\"></sup> and the priest shall pronounce them unclean. He is not to isolate them, because they are already unclean.",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>“If the disease breaks out all over their skin and, so far as the priest can see, it covers all the skin of the affected person from head to foot,",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>the priest is to examine them, and if the disease has covered their whole body, he shall pronounce them clean. Since it has all turned white, they are clean.",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>But whenever raw flesh appears on them, they will be unclean.",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>When the priest sees the raw flesh, he shall pronounce them unclean. The raw flesh is unclean; they have a defiling disease.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3068O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3068O\"></sup>",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>If the raw flesh changes and turns white, they must go to the priest.",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>The priest is to examine them, and if the sores have turned white, the priest shall pronounce the affected person clean;<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3070P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3070P\"></sup> then they will be clean.",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>“When someone has a boil<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3071Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3071Q\"></sup> on their skin and it heals,",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>and in the place where the boil was, a white swelling or reddish-white<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3072R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3072R\"></sup> spot<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3072S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3072S\"></sup> appears, they must present themselves to the priest.",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>The priest is to examine it, and if it appears to be more than skin deep and the hair in it has turned white, the priest shall pronounce that person unclean. It is a defiling skin disease<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3073T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3073T\"></sup> that has broken out where the boil was.",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>But if, when the priest examines it, there is no white hair in it and it is not more than skin deep and has faded, then the priest is to isolate them for seven days.",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>If it is spreading in the skin, the priest shall pronounce them unclean; it is a defiling disease.",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>But if the spot is unchanged and has not spread, it is only a scar from the boil, and the priest shall pronounce them clean.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3076U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3076U\"></sup>",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup>“When someone has a burn on their skin and a reddish-white or white spot appears in the raw flesh of the burn,",
			"25": "<sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup>the priest is to examine the spot, and if the hair in it has turned white, and it appears to be more than skin deep, it is a defiling disease that has broken out in the burn. The priest shall pronounce them unclean; it is a defiling skin disease.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3078V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3078V\"></sup>",
			"26": "<sup class=\"versenum\">26 </sup>But if the priest examines it and there is no white hair in the spot and if it is not more than skin deep and has faded, then the priest is to isolate them for seven days.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3079W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3079W\"></sup>",
			"27": "<sup class=\"versenum\">27 </sup>On the seventh day the priest is to examine that person,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3080X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3080X\"></sup> and if it is spreading in the skin, the priest shall pronounce them unclean; it is a defiling skin disease.",
			"28": "<sup class=\"versenum\">28 </sup>If, however, the spot is unchanged and has not spread in the skin but has faded, it is a swelling from the burn, and the priest shall pronounce them clean; it is only a scar from the burn.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3081Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3081Y\"></sup>",
			"29": "<sup class=\"versenum\">29 </sup>“If a man or woman has a sore on their head<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3082Z&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Z&quot;&gt;Z&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3082Z\"></sup> or chin,",
			"30": "<sup class=\"versenum\">30 </sup>the priest is to examine the sore, and if it appears to be more than skin deep and the hair in it is yellow and thin, the priest shall pronounce them unclean; it is a defiling skin disease on the head or chin.",
			"31": "<sup class=\"versenum\">31 </sup>But if, when the priest examines the sore, it does not seem to be more than skin deep and there is no black hair in it, then the priest is to isolate the affected person for seven days.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3084AA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AA&quot;&gt;AA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3084AA\"></sup>",
			"32": "<sup class=\"versenum\">32 </sup>On the seventh day the priest is to examine the sore,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3085AB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AB&quot;&gt;AB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3085AB\"></sup> and if it has not spread and there is no yellow hair in it and it does not appear to be more than skin deep,",
			"33": "<sup class=\"versenum\">33 </sup>then the man or woman must shave themselves, except for the affected area, and the priest is to keep them isolated another seven days.",
			"34": "<sup class=\"versenum\">34 </sup>On the seventh day the priest is to examine the sore,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3087AC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AC&quot;&gt;AC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3087AC\"></sup> and if it has not spread in the skin and appears to be no more than skin deep, the priest shall pronounce them clean. They must wash their clothes, and they will be clean.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3087AD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AD&quot;&gt;AD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3087AD\"></sup>",
			"35": "<sup class=\"versenum\">35 </sup>But if the sore does spread in the skin after they are pronounced clean,",
			"36": "<sup class=\"versenum\">36 </sup>the priest is to examine them, and if he finds that the sore has spread in the skin, he does not need to look for yellow hair; they are unclean.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3089AE&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AE&quot;&gt;AE&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3089AE\"></sup>",
			"37": "<sup class=\"versenum\">37 </sup>If, however, the sore is unchanged so far as the priest can see, and if black hair has grown in it, the affected person is healed. They are clean, and the priest shall pronounce them clean.",
			"38": "<sup class=\"versenum\">38 </sup>“When a man or woman has white spots on the skin,",
			"39": "<sup class=\"versenum\">39 </sup>the priest is to examine them, and if the spots are dull white, it is a harmless rash that has broken out on the skin; they are clean.",
			"40": "<sup class=\"versenum\">40 </sup>“A man who has lost his hair and is bald<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3093AF&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AF&quot;&gt;AF&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3093AF\"></sup> is clean.",
			"41": "<sup class=\"versenum\">41 </sup>If he has lost his hair from the front of his scalp and has a bald forehead, he is clean.",
			"42": "<sup class=\"versenum\">42 </sup>But if he has a reddish-white sore on his bald head or forehead, it is a defiling disease breaking out on his head or forehead.",
			"43": "<sup class=\"versenum\">43 </sup>The priest is to examine him, and if the swollen sore on his head or forehead is reddish-white like a defiling skin disease,",
			"44": "<sup class=\"versenum\">44 </sup>the man is diseased and is unclean. The priest shall pronounce him unclean because of the sore on his head.",
			"45": "<sup class=\"versenum\">45 </sup>“Anyone with such a defiling disease must wear torn clothes,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3098AG&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AG&quot;&gt;AG&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3098AG\"></sup> let their hair be unkempt, cover the lower part of their face<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3098AH&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AH&quot;&gt;AH&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3098AH\"></sup> and cry out, ‘Unclean! Unclean!’<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3098AI&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AI&quot;&gt;AI&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3098AI\"></sup>",
			"46": "<sup class=\"versenum\">46 </sup>As long as they have the disease they remain unclean. They must live alone; they must live outside the camp.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3099AJ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AJ&quot;&gt;AJ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3099AJ\"></sup>",
			"47": "<sup class=\"versenum\">47 </sup>“As for any fabric that is spoiled with a defiling mold—any woolen or linen clothing,",
			"48": "<sup class=\"versenum\">48 </sup>any woven or knitted material of linen or wool, any leather or anything made of leather—",
			"49": "<sup class=\"versenum\">49 </sup>if the affected area in the fabric, the leather, the woven or knitted material, or any leather article, is greenish or reddish, it is a defiling mold and must be shown to the priest.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3102AK&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AK&quot;&gt;AK&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3102AK\"></sup>",
			"50": "<sup class=\"versenum\">50 </sup>The priest is to examine the affected area<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3103AL&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AL&quot;&gt;AL&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3103AL\"></sup> and isolate the article for seven days.",
			"51": "<sup class=\"versenum\">51 </sup>On the seventh day he is to examine it,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3104AM&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AM&quot;&gt;AM&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3104AM\"></sup> and if the mold has spread in the fabric, the woven or knitted material, or the leather, whatever its use, it is a persistent defiling mold; the article is unclean.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3104AN&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AN&quot;&gt;AN&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3104AN\"></sup>",
			"52": "<sup class=\"versenum\">52 </sup>He must burn the fabric, the woven or knitted material of wool or linen, or any leather article that has been spoiled; because the defiling mold is persistent, the article must be burned.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3105AO&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AO&quot;&gt;AO&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3105AO\"></sup>",
			"53": "<sup class=\"versenum\">53 </sup>“But if, when the priest examines it, the mold has not spread in the fabric, the woven or knitted material, or the leather article,",
			"54": "<sup class=\"versenum\">54 </sup>he shall order that the spoiled article be washed. Then he is to isolate it for another seven days.",
			"55": "<sup class=\"versenum\">55 </sup>After the article has been washed, the priest is to examine it again, and if the mold has not changed its appearance, even though it has not spread, it is unclean. Burn it, no matter which side of the fabric has been spoiled.",
			"56": "<sup class=\"versenum\">56 </sup>If, when the priest examines it, the mold has faded after the article has been washed, he is to tear the spoiled part out of the fabric, the leather, or the woven or knitted material.",
			"57": "<sup class=\"versenum\">57 </sup>But if it reappears in the fabric, in the woven or knitted material, or in the leather article, it is a spreading mold; whatever has the mold must be burned.",
			"58": "<sup class=\"versenum\">58 </sup>Any fabric, woven or knitted material, or any leather article that has been washed and is rid of the mold, must be washed again. Then it will be clean.”",
			"59": "<sup class=\"versenum\">59 </sup>These are the regulations concerning defiling molds in woolen or linen clothing, woven or knitted material, or any leather article, for pronouncing them clean or unclean."
		},
		"14": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">14 </span>The <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> said to Moses,",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>“These are the regulations for any diseased person at the time of their ceremonial cleansing, when they are brought to the priest:<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3114A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3114A\"></sup>",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>The priest is to go outside the camp and examine them.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3115B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3115B\"></sup> If they have been healed of their defiling skin disease,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3115C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3115C\"></sup>",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>the priest shall order that two live clean birds and some cedar wood, scarlet yarn and hyssop<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3116D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3116D\"></sup> be brought for the person to be cleansed.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3116E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3116E\"></sup>",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>Then the priest shall order that one of the birds be killed over fresh water in a clay pot.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3117F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3117F\"></sup>",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>He is then to take the live bird and dip it, together with the cedar wood, the scarlet yarn and the hyssop, into the blood of the bird that was killed over the fresh water.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3118G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3118G\"></sup>",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>Seven times<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3119H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3119H\"></sup> he shall sprinkle<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3119I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3119I\"></sup> the one to be cleansed of the defiling disease, and then pronounce them clean. After that, he is to release the live bird in the open fields.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3119J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3119J\"></sup>",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>“The person to be cleansed must wash their clothes,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3120K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3120K\"></sup> shave off all their hair and bathe with water;<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3120L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3120L\"></sup> then they will be ceremonially clean.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3120M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3120M\"></sup> After this they may come into the camp,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3120N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3120N\"></sup> but they must stay outside their tent for seven days.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>On the seventh day<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3121O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3121O\"></sup> they must shave off all their hair;<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3121P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3121P\"></sup> they must shave their head, their beard, their eyebrows and the rest of their hair. They must wash their clothes and bathe themselves with water, and they will be clean.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3121Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3121Q\"></sup>",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>“On the eighth day<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3122R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3122R\"></sup> they must bring two male lambs and one ewe lamb<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3122S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3122S\"></sup> a year old, each without defect, along with three-tenths of an ephah<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3122T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3122T\"></sup> of the finest flour mixed with olive oil for a grain offering,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3122U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3122U\"></sup> and one log of oil.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3122V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3122V\"></sup>",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>The priest who pronounces them clean shall present<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3123W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3123W\"></sup> both the one to be cleansed and their offerings before the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> at the entrance to the tent of meeting.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3123X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3123X\"></sup>",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>“Then the priest is to take one of the male lambs and offer it as a guilt offering,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3124Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3124Y\"></sup> along with the log of oil; he shall wave them before the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> as a wave offering.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3124Z&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Z&quot;&gt;Z&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3124Z\"></sup>",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>He is to slaughter the lamb in the sanctuary area<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3125AA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AA&quot;&gt;AA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3125AA\"></sup> where the sin offering and the burnt offering are slaughtered. Like the sin offering, the guilt offering belongs to the priest;<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3125AB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AB&quot;&gt;AB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3125AB\"></sup> it is most holy.",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>The priest is to take some of the blood of the guilt offering and put it on the lobe of the right ear of the one to be cleansed, on the thumb of their right hand and on the big toe of their right foot.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3126AC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AC&quot;&gt;AC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3126AC\"></sup>",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>The priest shall then take some of the log of oil, pour it in the palm of his own left hand,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3127AD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AD&quot;&gt;AD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3127AD\"></sup>",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>dip his right forefinger into the oil in his palm, and with his finger sprinkle some of it before the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> seven times.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3128AE&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AE&quot;&gt;AE&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3128AE\"></sup>",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>The priest is to put some of the oil remaining in his palm on the lobe of the right ear of the one to be cleansed, on the thumb of their right hand and on the big toe of their right foot, on top of the blood of the guilt offering.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3129AF&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AF&quot;&gt;AF&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3129AF\"></sup>",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>The rest of the oil in his palm the priest shall put on the head of the one to be cleansed<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3130AG&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AG&quot;&gt;AG&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3130AG\"></sup> and make atonement for them before the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>“Then the priest is to sacrifice the sin offering and make atonement for the one to be cleansed from their uncleanness.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3131AH&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AH&quot;&gt;AH&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3131AH\"></sup> After that, the priest shall slaughter the burnt offering",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>and offer it on the altar, together with the grain offering, and make atonement for them,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3132AI&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AI&quot;&gt;AI&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3132AI\"></sup> and they will be clean.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3132AJ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AJ&quot;&gt;AJ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3132AJ\"></sup>",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>“If, however, they are poor<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3133AK&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AK&quot;&gt;AK&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3133AK\"></sup> and cannot afford these,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3133AL&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AL&quot;&gt;AL&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3133AL\"></sup> they must take one male lamb as a guilt offering to be waved to make atonement for them, together with a tenth of an ephah of the finest flour mixed with olive oil for a grain offering, a log of oil,",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>and two doves or two young pigeons,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3134AM&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AM&quot;&gt;AM&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3134AM\"></sup> such as they can afford, one for a sin offering and the other for a burnt offering.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3134AN&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AN&quot;&gt;AN&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3134AN\"></sup>",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>“On the eighth day they must bring them for their cleansing to the priest at the entrance to the tent of meeting,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3135AO&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AO&quot;&gt;AO&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3135AO\"></sup> before the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3135AP&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AP&quot;&gt;AP&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3135AP\"></sup>",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup>The priest is to take the lamb for the guilt offering,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3136AQ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AQ&quot;&gt;AQ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3136AQ\"></sup> together with the log of oil,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3136AR&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AR&quot;&gt;AR&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3136AR\"></sup> and wave them before the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> as a wave offering.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3136AS&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AS&quot;&gt;AS&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3136AS\"></sup>",
			"25": "<sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup>He shall slaughter the lamb for the guilt offering and take some of its blood and put it on the lobe of the right ear of the one to be cleansed, on the thumb of their right hand and on the big toe of their right foot.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3137AT&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AT&quot;&gt;AT&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3137AT\"></sup>",
			"26": "<sup class=\"versenum\">26 </sup>The priest is to pour some of the oil into the palm of his own left hand,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3138AU&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AU&quot;&gt;AU&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3138AU\"></sup>",
			"27": "<sup class=\"versenum\">27 </sup>and with his right forefinger sprinkle some of the oil from his palm seven times before the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.",
			"28": "<sup class=\"versenum\">28 </sup>Some of the oil in his palm he is to put on the same places he put the blood of the guilt offering—on the lobe of the right ear of the one to be cleansed, on the thumb of their right hand and on the big toe of their right foot.",
			"29": "<sup class=\"versenum\">29 </sup>The rest of the oil in his palm the priest shall put on the head of the one to be cleansed, to make atonement for them before the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3141AV&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AV&quot;&gt;AV&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3141AV\"></sup>",
			"30": "<sup class=\"versenum\">30 </sup>Then he shall sacrifice the doves or the young pigeons, such as the person can afford,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3142AW&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AW&quot;&gt;AW&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3142AW\"></sup>",
			"31": "<sup class=\"versenum\">31 </sup>one as a sin offering and the other as a burnt offering,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3143AX&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AX&quot;&gt;AX&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3143AX\"></sup> together with the grain offering. In this way the priest will make atonement before the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> on behalf of the one to be cleansed.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3143AY&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AY&quot;&gt;AY&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3143AY\"></sup>”",
			"32": "<sup class=\"versenum\">32 </sup>These are the regulations for anyone who has a defiling skin disease<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3144AZ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AZ&quot;&gt;AZ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3144AZ\"></sup> and who cannot afford the regular offerings<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3144BA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BA&quot;&gt;BA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3144BA\"></sup> for their cleansing.",
			"33": "<sup class=\"versenum\">33 </sup>The <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> said to Moses and Aaron,",
			"34": "<sup class=\"versenum\">34 </sup>“When you enter the land of Canaan,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3146BB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BB&quot;&gt;BB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3146BB\"></sup> which I am giving you as your possession,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3146BC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BC&quot;&gt;BC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3146BC\"></sup> and I put a spreading mold in a house in that land,",
			"35": "<sup class=\"versenum\">35 </sup>the owner of the house must go and tell the priest, ‘I have seen something that looks like a defiling mold in my house.’",
			"36": "<sup class=\"versenum\">36 </sup>The priest is to order the house to be emptied before he goes in to examine the mold, so that nothing in the house will be pronounced unclean. After this the priest is to go in and inspect the house.",
			"37": "<sup class=\"versenum\">37 </sup>He is to examine the mold on the walls, and if it has greenish or reddish<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3149BD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BD&quot;&gt;BD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3149BD\"></sup> depressions that appear to be deeper than the surface of the wall,",
			"38": "<sup class=\"versenum\">38 </sup>the priest shall go out the doorway of the house and close it up for seven days.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3150BE&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BE&quot;&gt;BE&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3150BE\"></sup>",
			"39": "<sup class=\"versenum\">39 </sup>On the seventh day<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3151BF&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BF&quot;&gt;BF&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3151BF\"></sup> the priest shall return to inspect the house. If the mold has spread on the walls,",
			"40": "<sup class=\"versenum\">40 </sup>he is to order that the contaminated stones be torn out and thrown into an unclean place outside the town.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3152BG&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BG&quot;&gt;BG&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3152BG\"></sup>",
			"41": "<sup class=\"versenum\">41 </sup>He must have all the inside walls of the house scraped and the material that is scraped off dumped into an unclean place outside the town.",
			"42": "<sup class=\"versenum\">42 </sup>Then they are to take other stones to replace these and take new clay and plaster the house.",
			"43": "<sup class=\"versenum\">43 </sup>“If the defiling mold reappears in the house after the stones have been torn out and the house scraped and plastered,",
			"44": "<sup class=\"versenum\">44 </sup>the priest is to go and examine it and, if the mold has spread in the house, it is a persistent defiling mold; the house is unclean.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3156BH&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BH&quot;&gt;BH&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3156BH\"></sup>",
			"45": "<sup class=\"versenum\">45 </sup>It must be torn down—its stones, timbers and all the plaster—and taken out of the town to an unclean place.",
			"46": "<sup class=\"versenum\">46 </sup>“Anyone who goes into the house while it is closed up will be unclean till evening.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3158BI&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BI&quot;&gt;BI&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3158BI\"></sup>",
			"47": "<sup class=\"versenum\">47 </sup>Anyone who sleeps or eats in the house must wash their clothes.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3159BJ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BJ&quot;&gt;BJ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3159BJ\"></sup>",
			"48": "<sup class=\"versenum\">48 </sup>“But if the priest comes to examine it and the mold has not spread after the house has been plastered, he shall pronounce the house clean,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3160BK&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BK&quot;&gt;BK&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3160BK\"></sup> because the defiling mold is gone.",
			"49": "<sup class=\"versenum\">49 </sup>To purify the house he is to take two birds and some cedar wood, scarlet yarn and hyssop.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3161BL&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BL&quot;&gt;BL&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3161BL\"></sup>",
			"50": "<sup class=\"versenum\">50 </sup>He shall kill one of the birds over fresh water in a clay pot.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3162BM&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BM&quot;&gt;BM&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3162BM\"></sup>",
			"51": "<sup class=\"versenum\">51 </sup>Then he is to take the cedar wood, the hyssop,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3163BN&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BN&quot;&gt;BN&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3163BN\"></sup> the scarlet yarn and the live bird, dip them into the blood of the dead bird and the fresh water, and sprinkle the house seven times.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3163BO&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BO&quot;&gt;BO&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3163BO\"></sup>",
			"52": "<sup class=\"versenum\">52 </sup>He shall purify the house with the bird’s blood, the fresh water, the live bird, the cedar wood, the hyssop and the scarlet yarn.",
			"53": "<sup class=\"versenum\">53 </sup>Then he is to release the live bird in the open fields<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3165BP&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BP&quot;&gt;BP&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3165BP\"></sup> outside the town. In this way he will make atonement for the house, and it will be clean.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3165BQ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BQ&quot;&gt;BQ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3165BQ\"></sup>”",
			"54": "<sup class=\"versenum\">54 </sup>These are the regulations for any defiling skin disease,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3166BR&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BR&quot;&gt;BR&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3166BR\"></sup> for a sore,",
			"55": "<sup class=\"versenum\">55 </sup>for defiling molds<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3167BS&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BS&quot;&gt;BS&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3167BS\"></sup> in fabric or in a house,",
			"56": "<sup class=\"versenum\">56 </sup>and for a swelling, a rash or a shiny spot,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3168BT&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BT&quot;&gt;BT&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3168BT\"></sup>",
			"57": "<sup class=\"versenum\">57 </sup>to determine when something is clean or unclean.These are the regulations for defiling skin diseases and defiling molds.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3169BU&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BU&quot;&gt;BU&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3169BU\"></sup>"
		},
		"15": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">15 </span>The <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> said to Moses and Aaron,",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>“Speak to the Israelites and say to them: ‘When any man has an unusual bodily discharge,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3171A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3171A\"></sup> such a discharge is unclean.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>Whether it continues flowing from his body or is blocked, it will make him unclean. This is how his discharge will bring about uncleanness:",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>“‘Any bed the man with a discharge lies on will be unclean, and anything he sits on will be unclean.",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>Anyone who touches his bed must wash their clothes<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3174B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3174B\"></sup> and bathe with water,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3174C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3174C\"></sup> and they will be unclean till evening.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3174D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3174D\"></sup>",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>Whoever sits on anything that the man with a discharge sat on must wash their clothes and bathe with water, and they will be unclean till evening.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>“‘Whoever touches the man<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3176E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3176E\"></sup> who has a discharge<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3176F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3176F\"></sup> must wash their clothes and bathe with water, and they will be unclean till evening.",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>“‘If the man with the discharge spits<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3177G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3177G\"></sup> on anyone who is clean, they must wash their clothes and bathe with water, and they will be unclean till evening.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>“‘Everything the man sits on when riding will be unclean,",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>and whoever touches any of the things that were under him will be unclean till evening; whoever picks up those things<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3179H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3179H\"></sup> must wash their clothes and bathe with water, and they will be unclean till evening.",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>“‘Anyone the man with a discharge touches without rinsing his hands with water must wash their clothes and bathe with water, and they will be unclean till evening.",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>“‘A clay pot<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3181I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3181I\"></sup> that the man touches must be broken, and any wooden article<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3181J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3181J\"></sup> is to be rinsed with water.",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>“‘When a man is cleansed from his discharge, he is to count off seven days<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3182K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3182K\"></sup> for his ceremonial cleansing; he must wash his clothes and bathe himself with fresh water, and he will be clean.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3182L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3182L\"></sup>",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>On the eighth day he must take two doves or two young pigeons<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3183M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3183M\"></sup> and come before the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> to the entrance to the tent of meeting and give them to the priest.",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>The priest is to sacrifice them, the one for a sin offering<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3184N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3184N\"></sup> and the other for a burnt offering.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3184O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3184O\"></sup> In this way he will make atonement before the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> for the man because of his discharge.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3184P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3184P\"></sup>",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>“‘When a man has an emission of semen,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3185Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3185Q\"></sup> he must bathe his whole body with water, and he will be unclean till evening.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3185R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3185R\"></sup>",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>Any clothing or leather that has semen on it must be washed with water, and it will be unclean till evening.",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>When a man has sexual relations with a woman and there is an emission of semen,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3187S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3187S\"></sup> both of them must bathe with water, and they will be unclean till evening.",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>“‘When a woman has her regular flow of blood, the impurity of her monthly period<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3188T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3188T\"></sup> will last seven days, and anyone who touches her will be unclean till evening.",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>“‘Anything she lies on during her period will be unclean, and anything she sits on will be unclean.",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>Anyone who touches her bed will be unclean; they must wash their clothes and bathe with water, and they will be unclean till evening.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3190U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3190U\"></sup>",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>Anyone who touches anything she sits on will be unclean; they must wash their clothes and bathe with water, and they will be unclean till evening.",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>Whether it is the bed or anything she was sitting on, when anyone touches it, they will be unclean till evening.",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup>“‘If a man has sexual relations with her and her monthly flow<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3193V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3193V\"></sup> touches him, he will be unclean for seven days; any bed he lies on will be unclean.",
			"25": "<sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup>“‘When a woman has a discharge of blood for many days at a time other than her monthly period<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3194W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3194W\"></sup> or has a discharge that continues beyond her period, she will be unclean as long as she has the discharge, just as in the days of her period.",
			"26": "<sup class=\"versenum\">26 </sup>Any bed she lies on while her discharge continues will be unclean, as is her bed during her monthly period, and anything she sits on will be unclean, as during her period.",
			"27": "<sup class=\"versenum\">27 </sup>Anyone who touches them will be unclean; they must wash their clothes and bathe with water, and they will be unclean till evening.",
			"28": "<sup class=\"versenum\">28 </sup>“‘When she is cleansed from her discharge, she must count off seven days, and after that she will be ceremonially clean.",
			"29": "<sup class=\"versenum\">29 </sup>On the eighth day she must take two doves or two young pigeons<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3198X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3198X\"></sup> and bring them to the priest at the entrance to the tent of meeting.",
			"30": "<sup class=\"versenum\">30 </sup>The priest is to sacrifice one for a sin offering and the other for a burnt offering. In this way he will make atonement for her before the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> for the uncleanness of her discharge.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3199Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3199Y\"></sup>",
			"31": "<sup class=\"versenum\">31 </sup>“‘You must keep the Israelites separate from things that make them unclean, so they will not die in their uncleanness for defiling my dwelling place,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3200Z&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Z&quot;&gt;Z&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3200Z\"></sup> which is among them.’”",
			"32": "<sup class=\"versenum\">32 </sup>These are the regulations for a man with a discharge, for anyone made unclean by an emission of semen,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3201AA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AA&quot;&gt;AA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3201AA\"></sup>",
			"33": "<sup class=\"versenum\">33 </sup>for a woman in her monthly period, for a man or a woman with a discharge, and for a man who has sexual relations with a woman who is ceremonially unclean.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3202AB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AB&quot;&gt;AB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3202AB\"></sup>"
		},
		"16": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">16 </span>The <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> spoke to Moses after the death of the two sons of Aaron who died when they approached the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3203B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3203B\"></sup>",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>The <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> said to Moses: “Tell your brother Aaron that he is not to come whenever he chooses<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3204C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3204C\"></sup> into the Most Holy Place<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3204D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3204D\"></sup> behind the curtain<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3204E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3204E\"></sup> in front of the atonement cover<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3204F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3204F\"></sup> on the ark, or else he will die. For I will appear<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3204G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3204G\"></sup> in the cloud<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3204H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3204H\"></sup> over the atonement cover.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>“This is how Aaron is to enter the Most Holy Place:<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3205I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3205I\"></sup> He must first bring a young bull<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3205J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3205J\"></sup> for a sin offering and a ram for a burnt offering.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3205K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3205K\"></sup>",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>He is to put on the sacred linen tunic,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3206L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3206L\"></sup> with linen undergarments next to his body; he is to tie the linen sash around him and put on the linen turban.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3206M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3206M\"></sup> These are sacred garments;<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3206N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3206N\"></sup> so he must bathe himself with water<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3206O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3206O\"></sup> before he puts them on.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3206P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3206P\"></sup>",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>From the Israelite community<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3207Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3207Q\"></sup> he is to take two male goats<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3207R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3207R\"></sup> for a sin offering and a ram for a burnt offering.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>“Aaron is to offer the bull for his own sin offering to make atonement for himself and his household.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3208S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3208S\"></sup>",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>Then he is to take the two goats and present them before the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> at the entrance to the tent of meeting.",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>He is to cast lots<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3210T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3210T\"></sup> for the two goats—one lot for the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> and the other for the scapegoat.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3210U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3210U\"></sup>",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>Aaron shall bring the goat whose lot falls to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> and sacrifice it for a sin offering.",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>But the goat chosen by lot as the scapegoat shall be presented alive before the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> to be used for making atonement<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3212V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3212V\"></sup> by sending it into the wilderness as a scapegoat.",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>“Aaron shall bring the bull for his own sin offering to make atonement for himself and his household,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3213W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3213W\"></sup> and he is to slaughter the bull for his own sin offering.",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>He is to take a censer full of burning coals<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3214X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3214X\"></sup> from the altar before the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> and two handfuls of finely ground fragrant incense<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3214Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3214Y\"></sup> and take them behind the curtain.",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>He is to put the incense on the fire before the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, and the smoke of the incense will conceal the atonement cover<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3215Z&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Z&quot;&gt;Z&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3215Z\"></sup> above the tablets of the covenant law, so that he will not die.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3215AA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AA&quot;&gt;AA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3215AA\"></sup>",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>He is to take some of the bull’s blood<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3216AB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AB&quot;&gt;AB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3216AB\"></sup> and with his finger sprinkle it on the front of the atonement cover; then he shall sprinkle some of it with his finger seven times before the atonement cover.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3216AC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AC&quot;&gt;AC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3216AC\"></sup>",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>“He shall then slaughter the goat for the sin offering for the people<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3217AD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AD&quot;&gt;AD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3217AD\"></sup> and take its blood behind the curtain<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3217AE&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AE&quot;&gt;AE&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3217AE\"></sup> and do with it as he did with the bull’s blood: He shall sprinkle<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3217AF&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AF&quot;&gt;AF&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3217AF\"></sup> it on the atonement cover and in front of it.",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>In this way he will make atonement<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3218AG&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AG&quot;&gt;AG&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3218AG\"></sup> for the Most Holy Place<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3218AH&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AH&quot;&gt;AH&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3218AH\"></sup> because of the uncleanness and rebellion of the Israelites, whatever their sins have been. He is to do the same for the tent of meeting,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3218AI&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AI&quot;&gt;AI&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3218AI\"></sup> which is among them in the midst of their uncleanness.",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>No one is to be in the tent of meeting from the time Aaron goes in to make atonement in the Most Holy Place until he comes out, having made atonement for himself, his household and the whole community of Israel.",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>“Then he shall come out to the altar<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3220AJ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AJ&quot;&gt;AJ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3220AJ\"></sup> that is before the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> and make atonement for it. He shall take some of the bull’s blood and some of the goat’s blood and put it on all the horns of the altar.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3220AK&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AK&quot;&gt;AK&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3220AK\"></sup>",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>He shall sprinkle some of the blood on it with his finger seven times to cleanse it and to consecrate it from the uncleanness of the Israelites.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3221AL&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AL&quot;&gt;AL&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3221AL\"></sup>",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>“When Aaron has finished making atonement for the Most Holy Place, the tent of meeting and the altar, he shall bring forward the live goat.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3222AM&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AM&quot;&gt;AM&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3222AM\"></sup>",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>He is to lay both hands on the head of the live goat<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3223AN&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AN&quot;&gt;AN&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3223AN\"></sup> and confess<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3223AO&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AO&quot;&gt;AO&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3223AO\"></sup> over it all the wickedness and rebellion of the Israelites—all their sins—and put them on the goat’s head. He shall send the goat away into the wilderness in the care of someone appointed for the task.",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>The goat will carry on itself all their sins<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3224AP&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AP&quot;&gt;AP&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3224AP\"></sup> to a remote place; and the man shall release it in the wilderness.",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>“Then Aaron is to go into the tent of meeting and take off the linen garments<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3225AQ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AQ&quot;&gt;AQ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3225AQ\"></sup> he put on before he entered the Most Holy Place, and he is to leave them there.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3225AR&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AR&quot;&gt;AR&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3225AR\"></sup>",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup>He shall bathe himself with water in the sanctuary area<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3226AS&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AS&quot;&gt;AS&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3226AS\"></sup> and put on his regular garments.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3226AT&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AT&quot;&gt;AT&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3226AT\"></sup> Then he shall come out and sacrifice the burnt offering for himself and the burnt offering for the people,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3226AU&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AU&quot;&gt;AU&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3226AU\"></sup> to make atonement for himself and for the people.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3226AV&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AV&quot;&gt;AV&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3226AV\"></sup>",
			"25": "<sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup>He shall also burn the fat of the sin offering on the altar.",
			"26": "<sup class=\"versenum\">26 </sup>“The man who releases the goat as a scapegoat<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3228AW&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AW&quot;&gt;AW&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3228AW\"></sup> must wash his clothes<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3228AX&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AX&quot;&gt;AX&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3228AX\"></sup> and bathe himself with water;<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3228AY&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AY&quot;&gt;AY&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3228AY\"></sup> afterward he may come into the camp.",
			"27": "<sup class=\"versenum\">27 </sup>The bull and the goat for the sin offerings, whose blood was brought into the Most Holy Place to make atonement, must be taken outside the camp;<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3229AZ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AZ&quot;&gt;AZ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3229AZ\"></sup> their hides, flesh and intestines are to be burned up.",
			"28": "<sup class=\"versenum\">28 </sup>The man who burns them must wash his clothes and bathe himself with water; afterward he may come into the camp.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3230BA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BA&quot;&gt;BA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3230BA\"></sup>",
			"29": "<sup class=\"versenum\">29 </sup>“This is to be a lasting ordinance<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3231BB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BB&quot;&gt;BB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3231BB\"></sup> for you: On the tenth day of the seventh month<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3231BC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BC&quot;&gt;BC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3231BC\"></sup> you must deny yourselves<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3231BD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BD&quot;&gt;BD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3231BD\"></sup> and not do any work<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3231BE&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BE&quot;&gt;BE&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3231BE\"></sup>—whether native-born<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3231BF&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BF&quot;&gt;BF&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3231BF\"></sup> or a foreigner residing among you—",
			"30": "<sup class=\"versenum\">30 </sup>because on this day atonement will be made<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3232BG&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BG&quot;&gt;BG&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3232BG\"></sup> for you, to cleanse you. Then, before the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, you will be clean from all your sins.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3232BH&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BH&quot;&gt;BH&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3232BH\"></sup>",
			"31": "<sup class=\"versenum\">31 </sup>It is a day of sabbath rest, and you must deny yourselves;<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3233BI&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BI&quot;&gt;BI&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3233BI\"></sup> it is a lasting ordinance.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3233BJ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BJ&quot;&gt;BJ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3233BJ\"></sup>",
			"32": "<sup class=\"versenum\">32 </sup>The priest who is anointed and ordained<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3234BK&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BK&quot;&gt;BK&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3234BK\"></sup> to succeed his father as high priest is to make atonement. He is to put on the sacred linen garments<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3234BL&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BL&quot;&gt;BL&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3234BL\"></sup>",
			"33": "<sup class=\"versenum\">33 </sup>and make atonement for the Most Holy Place, for the tent of meeting and the altar, and for the priests and all the members of the community.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3235BM&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BM&quot;&gt;BM&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3235BM\"></sup>",
			"34": "<sup class=\"versenum\">34 </sup>“This is to be a lasting ordinance<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3236BN&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BN&quot;&gt;BN&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3236BN\"></sup> for you: Atonement is to be made once a year<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3236BO&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BO&quot;&gt;BO&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3236BO\"></sup> for all the sins of the Israelites.”And it was done, as the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> commanded Moses."
		},
		"17": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">17 </span>The <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> said to Moses,",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>“Speak to Aaron and his sons<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3238A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3238A\"></sup> and to all the Israelites and say to them: ‘This is what the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> has commanded:",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>Any Israelite who sacrifices an ox, a lamb<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3239B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3239B\"></sup> or a goat<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3239C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3239C\"></sup> in the camp or outside of it",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>instead of bringing it to the entrance to the tent of meeting<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3240D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3240D\"></sup> to present it as an offering to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> in front of the tabernacle of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3240E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3240E\"></sup>—that person shall be considered guilty of bloodshed; they have shed blood and must be cut off from their people.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3240F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3240F\"></sup>",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>This is so the Israelites will bring to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> the sacrifices they are now making in the open fields. They must bring them to the priest, that is, to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, at the entrance to the tent of meeting and sacrifice them as fellowship offerings.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3241G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3241G\"></sup>",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>The priest is to splash the blood against the altar<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3242H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3242H\"></sup> of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3242I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3242I\"></sup> at the entrance to the tent of meeting and burn the fat as an aroma pleasing to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3242J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3242J\"></sup>",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>They must no longer offer any of their sacrifices to the goat idols<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3243K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3243K\"></sup> to whom they prostitute themselves.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3243L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3243L\"></sup> This is to be a lasting ordinance<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3243M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3243M\"></sup> for them and for the generations to come.’<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3243N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3243N\"></sup>",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>“Say to them: ‘Any Israelite or any foreigner residing among them who offers a burnt offering or sacrifice",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>and does not bring it to the entrance to the tent<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3245O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3245O\"></sup> of meeting<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3245P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3245P\"></sup> to sacrifice it to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3245Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3245Q\"></sup> must be cut off from the people of Israel.",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>“‘I will set my face against any Israelite or any foreigner residing among them who eats blood,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3246R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3246R\"></sup> and I will cut them off from the people.",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>For the life of a creature is in the blood,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3247S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3247S\"></sup> and I have given it to you to make atonement for yourselves on the altar; it is the blood that makes atonement for one’s life.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3247T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3247T\"></sup>",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>Therefore I say to the Israelites, “None of you may eat blood, nor may any foreigner residing among you eat blood.”",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>“‘Any Israelite or any foreigner residing among you who hunts any animal or bird that may be eaten must drain out the blood and cover it with earth,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3249U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3249U\"></sup>",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>because the life of every creature is its blood. That is why I have said to the Israelites, “You must not eat the blood of any creature, because the life of every creature is its blood; anyone who eats it must be cut off.”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3250V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3250V\"></sup>",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>“‘Anyone, whether native-born or foreigner, who eats anything<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3251W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3251W\"></sup> found dead or torn by wild animals<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3251X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3251X\"></sup> must wash their clothes and bathe with water,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3251Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3251Y\"></sup> and they will be ceremonially unclean till evening;<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3251Z&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Z&quot;&gt;Z&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3251Z\"></sup> then they will be clean.",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>But if they do not wash their clothes and bathe themselves, they will be held responsible.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3252AA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AA&quot;&gt;AA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3252AA\"></sup>’”"
		},
		"18": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">18 </span>The <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> said to Moses,",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>“Speak to the Israelites and say to them: ‘I am the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3254A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3254A\"></sup>",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>You must not do as they do in Egypt, where you used to live, and you must not do as they do in the land of Canaan, where I am bringing you. Do not follow their practices.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3255B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3255B\"></sup>",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>You must obey my laws<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3256C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3256C\"></sup> and be careful to follow my decrees.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3256D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3256D\"></sup> I am the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3256E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3256E\"></sup>",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>Keep my decrees and laws,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3257F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3257F\"></sup> for the person who obeys them will live by them.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3257G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3257G\"></sup> I am the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>“‘No one is to approach any close relative to have sexual relations. I am the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>“‘Do not dishonor your father<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3259H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3259H\"></sup> by having sexual relations with your mother.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3259I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3259I\"></sup> She is your mother; do not have relations with her.",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>“‘Do not have sexual relations with your father’s wife;<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3260J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3260J\"></sup> that would dishonor your father.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3260K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3260K\"></sup>",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>“‘Do not have sexual relations with your sister,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3261L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3261L\"></sup> either your father’s daughter or your mother’s daughter, whether she was born in the same home or elsewhere.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3261M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3261M\"></sup>",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>“‘Do not have sexual relations with your son’s daughter or your daughter’s daughter; that would dishonor you.",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>“‘Do not have sexual relations with the daughter of your father’s wife, born to your father; she is your sister.",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>“‘Do not have sexual relations with your father’s sister;<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3264N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3264N\"></sup> she is your father’s close relative.",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>“‘Do not have sexual relations with your mother’s sister,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3265O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3265O\"></sup> because she is your mother’s close relative.",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>“‘Do not dishonor your father’s brother by approaching his wife to have sexual relations; she is your aunt.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3266P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3266P\"></sup>",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>“‘Do not have sexual relations with your daughter-in-law.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3267Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3267Q\"></sup> She is your son’s wife; do not have relations with her.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3267R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3267R\"></sup>",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>“‘Do not have sexual relations with your brother’s wife;<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3268S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3268S\"></sup> that would dishonor your brother.",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>“‘Do not have sexual relations with both a woman and her daughter.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3269T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3269T\"></sup> Do not have sexual relations with either her son’s daughter or her daughter’s daughter; they are her close relatives. That is wickedness.",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>“‘Do not take your wife’s sister<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3270U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3270U\"></sup> as a rival wife and have sexual relations with her while your wife is living.",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>“‘Do not approach a woman to have sexual relations during the uncleanness<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3271V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3271V\"></sup> of her monthly period.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3271W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3271W\"></sup>",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>“‘Do not have sexual relations with your neighbor’s wife<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3272X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3272X\"></sup> and defile yourself with her.",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>“‘Do not give any of your children<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3273Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3273Y\"></sup> to be sacrificed to Molek,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3273Z&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Z&quot;&gt;Z&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3273Z\"></sup> for you must not profane the name of your God.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3273AA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AA&quot;&gt;AA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3273AA\"></sup> I am the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3273AB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AB&quot;&gt;AB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3273AB\"></sup>",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>“‘Do not have sexual relations with a man as one does with a woman;<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3274AC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AC&quot;&gt;AC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3274AC\"></sup> that is detestable.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3274AD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AD&quot;&gt;AD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3274AD\"></sup>",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>“‘Do not have sexual relations with an animal and defile yourself with it. A woman must not present herself to an animal to have sexual relations with it; that is a perversion.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3275AE&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AE&quot;&gt;AE&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3275AE\"></sup>",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup>“‘Do not defile yourselves in any of these ways, because this is how the nations that I am going to drive out before you<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3276AF&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AF&quot;&gt;AF&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3276AF\"></sup> became defiled.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3276AG&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AG&quot;&gt;AG&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3276AG\"></sup>",
			"25": "<sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup>Even the land was defiled;<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3277AH&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AH&quot;&gt;AH&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3277AH\"></sup> so I punished it for its sin,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3277AI&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AI&quot;&gt;AI&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3277AI\"></sup> and the land vomited out its inhabitants.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3277AJ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AJ&quot;&gt;AJ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3277AJ\"></sup>",
			"26": "<sup class=\"versenum\">26 </sup>But you must keep my decrees and my laws.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3278AK&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AK&quot;&gt;AK&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3278AK\"></sup> The native-born and the foreigners residing among you must not do any of these detestable things,",
			"27": "<sup class=\"versenum\">27 </sup>for all these things were done by the people who lived in the land before you, and the land became defiled.",
			"28": "<sup class=\"versenum\">28 </sup>And if you defile the land,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3280AL&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AL&quot;&gt;AL&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3280AL\"></sup> it will vomit you out<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3280AM&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AM&quot;&gt;AM&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3280AM\"></sup> as it vomited out the nations that were before you.",
			"29": "<sup class=\"versenum\">29 </sup>“‘Everyone who does any of these detestable things—such persons must be cut off from their people.",
			"30": "<sup class=\"versenum\">30 </sup>Keep my requirements<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3282AN&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AN&quot;&gt;AN&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3282AN\"></sup> and do not follow any of the detestable customs that were practiced before you came and do not defile yourselves with them. I am the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3282AO&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AO&quot;&gt;AO&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3282AO\"></sup>’”"
		},
		"19": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">19 </span>The <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> said to Moses,",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>“Speak to the entire assembly of Israel<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3284A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3284A\"></sup> and say to them: ‘Be holy because I, the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3284B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3284B\"></sup> am holy.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3284C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3284C\"></sup>",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>“‘Each of you must respect your mother and father,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3285D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3285D\"></sup> and you must observe my Sabbaths.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3285E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3285E\"></sup> I am the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3285F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3285F\"></sup>",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>“‘Do not turn to idols or make metal gods for yourselves.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3286G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3286G\"></sup> I am the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3286H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3286H\"></sup>",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>“‘When you sacrifice a fellowship offering to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, sacrifice it in such a way that it will be accepted on your behalf.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>It shall be eaten on the day you sacrifice it or on the next day; anything left over until the third day must be burned up.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3288I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3288I\"></sup>",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>If any of it is eaten on the third day, it is impure and will not be accepted.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3289J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3289J\"></sup>",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>Whoever eats it will be held responsible<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3290K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3290K\"></sup> because they have desecrated what is holy<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3290L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3290L\"></sup> to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>; they must be cut off from their people.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3290M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3290M\"></sup>",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>“‘When you reap the harvest of your land, do not reap to the very edges<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3291N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3291N\"></sup> of your field or gather the gleanings of your harvest.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3291O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3291O\"></sup>",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>Do not go over your vineyard a second time<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3292P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3292P\"></sup> or pick up the grapes that have fallen.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3292Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3292Q\"></sup> Leave them for the poor and the foreigner.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3292R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3292R\"></sup> I am the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God.",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>“‘Do not steal.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3293S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3293S\"></sup>“‘Do not lie.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3293T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3293T\"></sup>“‘Do not deceive one another.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3293U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3293U\"></sup>",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>“‘Do not swear falsely<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3294V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3294V\"></sup> by my name<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3294W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3294W\"></sup> and so profane<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3294X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3294X\"></sup> the name of your God. I am the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>“‘Do not defraud or rob<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3295Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3295Y\"></sup> your neighbor.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3295Z&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Z&quot;&gt;Z&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3295Z\"></sup>“‘Do not hold back the wages of a hired worker<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3295AA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AA&quot;&gt;AA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3295AA\"></sup> overnight.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3295AB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AB&quot;&gt;AB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3295AB\"></sup>",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>“‘Do not curse the deaf or put a stumbling block in front of the blind,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3296AC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AC&quot;&gt;AC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3296AC\"></sup> but fear your God.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3296AD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AD&quot;&gt;AD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3296AD\"></sup> I am the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>“‘Do not pervert justice;<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3297AE&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AE&quot;&gt;AE&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3297AE\"></sup> do not show partiality<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3297AF&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AF&quot;&gt;AF&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3297AF\"></sup> to the poor or favoritism to the great,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3297AG&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AG&quot;&gt;AG&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3297AG\"></sup> but judge your neighbor fairly.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3297AH&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AH&quot;&gt;AH&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3297AH\"></sup>",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>“‘Do not go about spreading slander<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3298AI&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AI&quot;&gt;AI&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3298AI\"></sup> among your people.“‘Do not do anything that endangers your neighbor’s life.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3298AJ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AJ&quot;&gt;AJ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3298AJ\"></sup> I am the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>“‘Do not hate a fellow Israelite in your heart.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3299AK&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AK&quot;&gt;AK&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3299AK\"></sup> Rebuke your neighbor frankly<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3299AL&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AL&quot;&gt;AL&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3299AL\"></sup> so you will not share in their guilt.",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>“‘Do not seek revenge<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3300AM&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AM&quot;&gt;AM&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3300AM\"></sup> or bear a grudge<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3300AN&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AN&quot;&gt;AN&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3300AN\"></sup> against anyone among your people,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3300AO&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AO&quot;&gt;AO&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3300AO\"></sup> but love your neighbor<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3300AP&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AP&quot;&gt;AP&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3300AP\"></sup> as yourself.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3300AQ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AQ&quot;&gt;AQ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3300AQ\"></sup> I am the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>“‘Keep my decrees.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3301AR&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AR&quot;&gt;AR&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3301AR\"></sup>“‘Do not mate different kinds of animals.“‘Do not plant your field with two kinds of seed.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3301AS&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AS&quot;&gt;AS&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3301AS\"></sup>“‘Do not wear clothing woven of two kinds of material.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3301AT&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AT&quot;&gt;AT&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3301AT\"></sup>",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>“‘If a man sleeps with a female slave who is promised to another man<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3302AU&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AU&quot;&gt;AU&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3302AU\"></sup> but who has not been ransomed or given her freedom, there must be due punishment. Yet they are not to be put to death, because she had not been freed.",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>The man, however, must bring a ram to the entrance to the tent of meeting for a guilt offering to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3303AV&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AV&quot;&gt;AV&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3303AV\"></sup>",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>With the ram of the guilt offering the priest is to make atonement for him before the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> for the sin he has committed, and his sin will be forgiven.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3304AW&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AW&quot;&gt;AW&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3304AW\"></sup>",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>“‘When you enter the land and plant any kind of fruit tree, regard its fruit as forbidden. For three years you are to consider it forbidden; it must not be eaten.",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup>In the fourth year all its fruit will be holy,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3306AX&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AX&quot;&gt;AX&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3306AX\"></sup> an offering of praise to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.",
			"25": "<sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup>But in the fifth year you may eat its fruit. In this way your harvest will be increased. I am the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God.",
			"26": "<sup class=\"versenum\">26 </sup>“‘Do not eat any meat with the blood still in it.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3308AY&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AY&quot;&gt;AY&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3308AY\"></sup>“‘Do not practice divination<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3308AZ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AZ&quot;&gt;AZ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3308AZ\"></sup> or seek omens.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3308BA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BA&quot;&gt;BA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3308BA\"></sup>",
			"27": "<sup class=\"versenum\">27 </sup>“‘Do not cut the hair at the sides of your head or clip off the edges of your beard.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3309BB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BB&quot;&gt;BB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3309BB\"></sup>",
			"28": "<sup class=\"versenum\">28 </sup>“‘Do not cut<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3310BC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BC&quot;&gt;BC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3310BC\"></sup> your bodies for the dead or put tattoo marks on yourselves. I am the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.",
			"29": "<sup class=\"versenum\">29 </sup>“‘Do not degrade your daughter by making her a prostitute,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3311BD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BD&quot;&gt;BD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3311BD\"></sup> or the land will turn to prostitution and be filled with wickedness.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3311BE&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BE&quot;&gt;BE&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3311BE\"></sup>",
			"30": "<sup class=\"versenum\">30 </sup>“‘Observe my Sabbaths<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3312BF&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BF&quot;&gt;BF&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3312BF\"></sup> and have reverence for my sanctuary. I am the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3312BG&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BG&quot;&gt;BG&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3312BG\"></sup>",
			"31": "<sup class=\"versenum\">31 </sup>“‘Do not turn to mediums<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3313BH&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BH&quot;&gt;BH&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3313BH\"></sup> or seek out spiritists,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3313BI&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BI&quot;&gt;BI&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3313BI\"></sup> for you will be defiled by them. I am the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God.",
			"32": "<sup class=\"versenum\">32 </sup>“‘Stand up in the presence of the aged, show respect<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3314BJ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BJ&quot;&gt;BJ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3314BJ\"></sup> for the elderly<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3314BK&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BK&quot;&gt;BK&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3314BK\"></sup> and revere your God.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3314BL&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BL&quot;&gt;BL&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3314BL\"></sup> I am the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3314BM&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BM&quot;&gt;BM&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3314BM\"></sup>",
			"33": "<sup class=\"versenum\">33 </sup>“‘When a foreigner resides among you in your land, do not mistreat them.",
			"34": "<sup class=\"versenum\">34 </sup>The foreigner residing among you must be treated as your native-born.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3316BN&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BN&quot;&gt;BN&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3316BN\"></sup> Love them as yourself,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3316BO&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BO&quot;&gt;BO&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3316BO\"></sup> for you were foreigners<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3316BP&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BP&quot;&gt;BP&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3316BP\"></sup> in Egypt.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3316BQ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BQ&quot;&gt;BQ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3316BQ\"></sup> I am the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God.",
			"35": "<sup class=\"versenum\">35 </sup>“‘Do not use dishonest standards when measuring length, weight or quantity.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3317BR&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BR&quot;&gt;BR&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3317BR\"></sup>",
			"36": "<sup class=\"versenum\">36 </sup>Use honest scales<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3318BS&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BS&quot;&gt;BS&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3318BS\"></sup> and honest weights, an honest ephah<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3318BT&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BT&quot;&gt;BT&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3318BT\"></sup> and an honest hin.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3318BU&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BU&quot;&gt;BU&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3318BU\"></sup> I am the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God, who brought you out of Egypt.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3318BV&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BV&quot;&gt;BV&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3318BV\"></sup>",
			"37": "<sup class=\"versenum\">37 </sup>“‘Keep all my decrees<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3319BW&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BW&quot;&gt;BW&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3319BW\"></sup> and all my laws<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3319BX&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BX&quot;&gt;BX&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3319BX\"></sup> and follow them. I am the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.’”"
		},
		"20": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">20 </span>The <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> said to Moses,",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>“Say to the Israelites: ‘Any Israelite or any foreigner residing in Israel who sacrifices any of his children to Molek is to be put to death.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3321A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3321A\"></sup> The members of the community are to stone him.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3321B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3321B\"></sup>",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>I myself will set my face against him and will cut him off from his people;<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3322C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3322C\"></sup> for by sacrificing his children to Molek, he has defiled<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3322D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3322D\"></sup> my sanctuary<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3322E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3322E\"></sup> and profaned my holy name.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3322F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3322F\"></sup>",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>If the members of the community close their eyes when that man sacrifices one of his children to Molek and if they fail to put him to death,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3323G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3323G\"></sup>",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>I myself will set my face against him and his family and will cut them off from their people together with all who follow him in prostituting themselves to Molek.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>“‘I will set my face against anyone who turns to mediums and spiritists to prostitute themselves by following them, and I will cut them off from their people.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3325H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3325H\"></sup>",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>“‘Consecrate yourselves<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3326I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3326I\"></sup> and be holy,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3326J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3326J\"></sup> because I am the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3326K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3326K\"></sup>",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>Keep my decrees<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3327L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3327L\"></sup> and follow them. I am the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, who makes you holy.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3327M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3327M\"></sup>",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>“‘Anyone who curses their father<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3328N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3328N\"></sup> or mother<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3328O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3328O\"></sup> is to be put to death.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3328P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3328P\"></sup> Because they have cursed their father or mother, their blood will be on their own head.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3328Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3328Q\"></sup>",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>“‘If a man commits adultery with another man’s wife<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3329R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3329R\"></sup>—with the wife of his neighbor—both the adulterer and the adulteress are to be put to death.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3329S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3329S\"></sup>",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>“‘If a man has sexual relations with his father’s wife, he has dishonored his father.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3330T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3330T\"></sup> Both the man and the woman are to be put to death; their blood will be on their own heads.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3330U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3330U\"></sup>",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>“‘If a man has sexual relations with his daughter-in-law,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3331V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3331V\"></sup> both of them are to be put to death. What they have done is a perversion; their blood will be on their own heads.",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>“‘If a man has sexual relations with a man as one does with a woman, both of them have done what is detestable.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3332W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3332W\"></sup> They are to be put to death; their blood will be on their own heads.",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>“‘If a man marries both a woman and her mother,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3333X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3333X\"></sup> it is wicked. Both he and they must be burned in the fire,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3333Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3333Y\"></sup> so that no wickedness will be among you.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3333Z&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Z&quot;&gt;Z&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3333Z\"></sup>",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>“‘If a man has sexual relations with an animal,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3334AA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AA&quot;&gt;AA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3334AA\"></sup> he is to be put to death,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3334AB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AB&quot;&gt;AB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3334AB\"></sup> and you must kill the animal.",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>“‘If a woman approaches an animal to have sexual relations with it, kill both the woman and the animal. They are to be put to death; their blood will be on their own heads.",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>“‘If a man marries his sister<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3336AC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AC&quot;&gt;AC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3336AC\"></sup>, the daughter of either his father or his mother, and they have sexual relations, it is a disgrace. They are to be publicly removed<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3336AD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AD&quot;&gt;AD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3336AD\"></sup> from their people. He has dishonored his sister and will be held responsible.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3336AE&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AE&quot;&gt;AE&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3336AE\"></sup>",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>“‘If a man has sexual relations with a woman during her monthly period,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3337AF&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AF&quot;&gt;AF&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3337AF\"></sup> he has exposed the source of her flow, and she has also uncovered it. Both of them are to be cut off from their people.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3337AG&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AG&quot;&gt;AG&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3337AG\"></sup>",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>“‘Do not have sexual relations with the sister of either your mother or your father,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3338AH&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AH&quot;&gt;AH&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3338AH\"></sup> for that would dishonor a close relative; both of you would be held responsible.",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>“‘If a man has sexual relations with his aunt,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3339AI&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AI&quot;&gt;AI&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3339AI\"></sup> he has dishonored his uncle. They will be held responsible; they will die childless.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3339AJ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AJ&quot;&gt;AJ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3339AJ\"></sup>",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>“‘If a man marries his brother’s wife,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3340AK&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AK&quot;&gt;AK&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3340AK\"></sup> it is an act of impurity; he has dishonored his brother. They will be childless.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3340AL&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AL&quot;&gt;AL&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3340AL\"></sup>",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>“‘Keep all my decrees and laws<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3341AM&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AM&quot;&gt;AM&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3341AM\"></sup> and follow them, so that the land<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3341AN&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AN&quot;&gt;AN&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3341AN\"></sup> where I am bringing you to live may not vomit you out.",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>You must not live according to the customs of the nations<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3342AO&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AO&quot;&gt;AO&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3342AO\"></sup> I am going to drive out before you.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3342AP&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AP&quot;&gt;AP&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3342AP\"></sup> Because they did all these things, I abhorred them.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3342AQ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AQ&quot;&gt;AQ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3342AQ\"></sup>",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup>But I said to you, “You will possess their land; I will give it to you as an inheritance, a land flowing with milk and honey.”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3343AR&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AR&quot;&gt;AR&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3343AR\"></sup> I am the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God, who has set you apart from the nations.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3343AS&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AS&quot;&gt;AS&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3343AS\"></sup>",
			"25": "<sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup>“‘You must therefore make a distinction between clean and unclean animals and between unclean and clean birds.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3344AT&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AT&quot;&gt;AT&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3344AT\"></sup> Do not defile yourselves by any animal or bird or anything that moves along the ground—those that I have set apart as unclean for you.",
			"26": "<sup class=\"versenum\">26 </sup>You are to be holy to me<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3345AU&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AU&quot;&gt;AU&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3345AU\"></sup> because I, the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, am holy,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3345AV&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AV&quot;&gt;AV&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3345AV\"></sup> and I have set you apart from the nations<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3345AW&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AW&quot;&gt;AW&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3345AW\"></sup> to be my own.",
			"27": "<sup class=\"versenum\">27 </sup>“‘A man or woman who is a medium<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3346AX&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AX&quot;&gt;AX&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3346AX\"></sup> or spiritist among you must be put to death.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3346AY&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AY&quot;&gt;AY&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3346AY\"></sup> You are to stone them;<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3346AZ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AZ&quot;&gt;AZ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3346AZ\"></sup> their blood will be on their own heads.’”"
		},
		"21": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">21 </span>The <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> said to Moses, “Speak to the priests, the sons of Aaron,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3347A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3347A\"></sup> and say to them: ‘A priest must not make himself ceremonially unclean<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3347B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3347B\"></sup> for any of his people who die,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3347C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3347C\"></sup>",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>except for a close relative, such as his mother or father,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3348D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3348D\"></sup> his son or daughter, his brother,",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>or an unmarried sister who is dependent on him since she has no husband—for her he may make himself unclean.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3349E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3349E\"></sup>",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>He must not make himself unclean for people related to him by marriage, and so defile himself.",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>“‘Priests must not shave<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3351F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3351F\"></sup> their heads or shave off the edges of their beards<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3351G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3351G\"></sup> or cut their bodies.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3351H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3351H\"></sup>",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>They must be holy to their God<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3352I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3352I\"></sup> and must not profane the name of their God.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3352J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3352J\"></sup> Because they present the food offerings to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3352K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3352K\"></sup> the food of their God,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3352L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3352L\"></sup> they are to be holy.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3352M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3352M\"></sup>",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>“‘They must not marry women defiled by prostitution or divorced from their husbands,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3353N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3353N\"></sup> because priests are holy to their God.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3353O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3353O\"></sup>",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>Regard them as holy,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3354P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3354P\"></sup> because they offer up the food of your God.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3354Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3354Q\"></sup> Consider them holy, because I the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> am holy—I who make you holy.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3354R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3354R\"></sup>",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>“‘If a priest’s daughter defiles herself by becoming a prostitute, she disgraces her father; she must be burned in the fire.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3355S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3355S\"></sup>",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>“‘The high priest, the one among his brothers who has had the anointing oil poured on his head<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3356T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3356T\"></sup> and who has been ordained to wear the priestly garments,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3356U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3356U\"></sup> must not let his hair become unkempt or tear his clothes.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3356V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3356V\"></sup>",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>He must not enter a place where there is a dead body.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3357W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3357W\"></sup> He must not make himself unclean,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3357X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3357X\"></sup> even for his father or mother,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3357Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3357Y\"></sup>",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>nor leave the sanctuary<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3358Z&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Z&quot;&gt;Z&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3358Z\"></sup> of his God or desecrate it, because he has been dedicated by the anointing oil<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3358AA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AA&quot;&gt;AA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3358AA\"></sup> of his God. I am the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>“‘The woman he marries must be a virgin.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3359AB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AB&quot;&gt;AB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3359AB\"></sup>",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>He must not marry a widow, a divorced woman, or a woman defiled by prostitution, but only a virgin from his own people,",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>so that he will not defile his offspring among his people. I am the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, who makes him holy.’”",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>The <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> said to Moses,",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>“Say to Aaron: ‘For the generations to come none of your descendants who has a defect<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3363AC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AC&quot;&gt;AC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3363AC\"></sup> may come near to offer the food of his God.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3363AD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AD&quot;&gt;AD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3363AD\"></sup>",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>No man who has any defect<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3364AE&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AE&quot;&gt;AE&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3364AE\"></sup> may come near: no man who is blind<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3364AF&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AF&quot;&gt;AF&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3364AF\"></sup> or lame,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3364AG&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AG&quot;&gt;AG&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3364AG\"></sup> disfigured or deformed;",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>no man with a crippled foot or hand,",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>or who is a hunchback or a dwarf, or who has any eye defect, or who has festering or running sores or damaged testicles.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3366AH&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AH&quot;&gt;AH&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3366AH\"></sup>",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>No descendant of Aaron the priest who has any defect<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3367AI&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AI&quot;&gt;AI&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3367AI\"></sup> is to come near to present the food offerings to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3367AJ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AJ&quot;&gt;AJ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3367AJ\"></sup> He has a defect; he must not come near to offer the food of his God.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3367AK&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AK&quot;&gt;AK&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3367AK\"></sup>",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>He may eat the most holy food of his God,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3368AL&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AL&quot;&gt;AL&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3368AL\"></sup> as well as the holy food;",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>yet because of his defect,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3369AM&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AM&quot;&gt;AM&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3369AM\"></sup> he must not go near the curtain or approach the altar, and so desecrate my sanctuary.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3369AN&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AN&quot;&gt;AN&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3369AN\"></sup> I am the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, who makes them holy.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3369AO&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AO&quot;&gt;AO&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3369AO\"></sup>’”",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup>So Moses told this to Aaron and his sons and to all the Israelites."
		},
		"22": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">22 </span>The <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> said to Moses,",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>“Tell Aaron and his sons to treat with respect the sacred offerings<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3372A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3372A\"></sup> the Israelites consecrate to me, so they will not profane my holy name.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3372B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3372B\"></sup> I am the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3372C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3372C\"></sup>",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>“Say to them: ‘For the generations to come, if any of your descendants is ceremonially unclean and yet comes near the sacred offerings that the Israelites consecrate to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3373D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3373D\"></sup> that person must be cut off from my presence.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3373E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3373E\"></sup> I am the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>“‘If a descendant of Aaron has a defiling skin disease or a bodily discharge,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3374F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3374F\"></sup> he may not eat the sacred offerings until he is cleansed. He will also be unclean if he touches something defiled by a corpse<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3374G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3374G\"></sup> or by anyone who has an emission of semen,",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>or if he touches any crawling thing<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3375H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3375H\"></sup> that makes him unclean, or any person<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3375I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3375I\"></sup> who makes him unclean, whatever the uncleanness may be.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>The one who touches any such thing will be unclean<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3376J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3376J\"></sup> till evening.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3376K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3376K\"></sup> He must not eat any of the sacred offerings unless he has bathed himself with water.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3376L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3376L\"></sup>",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>When the sun goes down, he will be clean, and after that he may eat the sacred offerings, for they are his food.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3377M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3377M\"></sup>",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>He must not eat anything found dead<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3378N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3378N\"></sup> or torn by wild animals,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3378O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3378O\"></sup> and so become unclean<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3378P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3378P\"></sup> through it. I am the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3378Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3378Q\"></sup>",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>“‘The priests are to perform my service<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3379R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3379R\"></sup> in such a way that they do not become guilty<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3379S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3379S\"></sup> and die<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3379T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3379T\"></sup> for treating it with contempt. I am the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, who makes them holy.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3379U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3379U\"></sup>",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>“‘No one outside a priest’s family may eat the sacred offering, nor may the guest of a priest or his hired worker eat it.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3380V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3380V\"></sup>",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>But if a priest buys a slave with money, or if slaves are born in his household, they may eat his food.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3381W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3381W\"></sup>",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>If a priest’s daughter marries anyone other than a priest, she may not eat any of the sacred contributions.",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>But if a priest’s daughter becomes a widow or is divorced, yet has no children, and she returns to live in her father’s household as in her youth, she may eat her father’s food. No unauthorized person, however, may eat it.",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>“‘Anyone who eats a sacred offering by mistake<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3384X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3384X\"></sup> must make restitution to the priest for the offering and add a fifth of the value<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3384Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3384Y\"></sup> to it.",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>The priests must not desecrate the sacred offerings<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3385Z&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Z&quot;&gt;Z&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3385Z\"></sup> the Israelites present to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3385AA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AA&quot;&gt;AA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3385AA\"></sup>",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>by allowing them to eat<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3386AB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AB&quot;&gt;AB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3386AB\"></sup> the sacred offerings and so bring upon them guilt<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3386AC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AC&quot;&gt;AC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3386AC\"></sup> requiring payment.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3386AD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AD&quot;&gt;AD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3386AD\"></sup> I am the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, who makes them holy.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3386AE&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AE&quot;&gt;AE&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3386AE\"></sup>’”",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>The <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> said to Moses,",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>“Speak to Aaron and his sons and to all the Israelites and say to them: ‘If any of you—whether an Israelite or a foreigner residing in Israel<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3388AF&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AF&quot;&gt;AF&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3388AF\"></sup>—presents a gift<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3388AG&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AG&quot;&gt;AG&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3388AG\"></sup> for a burnt offering to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, either to fulfill a vow<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3388AH&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AH&quot;&gt;AH&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3388AH\"></sup> or as a freewill offering,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3388AI&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AI&quot;&gt;AI&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3388AI\"></sup>",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>you must present a male without defect<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3389AJ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AJ&quot;&gt;AJ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3389AJ\"></sup> from the cattle, sheep or goats in order that it may be accepted on your behalf.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3389AK&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AK&quot;&gt;AK&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3389AK\"></sup>",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>Do not bring anything with a defect,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3390AL&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AL&quot;&gt;AL&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3390AL\"></sup> because it will not be accepted on your behalf.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3390AM&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AM&quot;&gt;AM&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3390AM\"></sup>",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>When anyone brings from the herd or flock<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3391AN&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AN&quot;&gt;AN&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3391AN\"></sup> a fellowship offering<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3391AO&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AO&quot;&gt;AO&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3391AO\"></sup> to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> to fulfill a special vow or as a freewill offering,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3391AP&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AP&quot;&gt;AP&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3391AP\"></sup> it must be without defect or blemish<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3391AQ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AQ&quot;&gt;AQ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3391AQ\"></sup> to be acceptable.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3391AR&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AR&quot;&gt;AR&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3391AR\"></sup>",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>Do not offer to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> the blind, the injured or the maimed, or anything with warts or festering or running sores. Do not place any of these on the altar as a food offering presented to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>You may, however, present as a freewill offering an ox or a sheep that is deformed or stunted, but it will not be accepted in fulfillment of a vow.",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup>You must not offer to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> an animal whose testicles are bruised, crushed, torn or cut.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3394AS&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AS&quot;&gt;AS&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3394AS\"></sup> You must not do this in your own land,",
			"25": "<sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup>and you must not accept such animals from the hand of a foreigner and offer them as the food of your God.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3395AT&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AT&quot;&gt;AT&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3395AT\"></sup> They will not be accepted on your behalf, because they are deformed and have defects.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3395AU&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AU&quot;&gt;AU&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3395AU\"></sup>’”",
			"26": "<sup class=\"versenum\">26 </sup>The <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> said to Moses,",
			"27": "<sup class=\"versenum\">27 </sup>“When a calf, a lamb or a goat<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3397AV&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AV&quot;&gt;AV&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3397AV\"></sup> is born, it is to remain with its mother for seven days.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3397AW&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AW&quot;&gt;AW&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3397AW\"></sup> From the eighth day<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3397AX&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AX&quot;&gt;AX&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3397AX\"></sup> on, it will be acceptable<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3397AY&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AY&quot;&gt;AY&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3397AY\"></sup> as a food offering presented to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.",
			"28": "<sup class=\"versenum\">28 </sup>Do not slaughter a cow or a sheep and its young on the same day.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3398AZ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AZ&quot;&gt;AZ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3398AZ\"></sup>",
			"29": "<sup class=\"versenum\">29 </sup>“When you sacrifice a thank offering<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3399BA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BA&quot;&gt;BA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3399BA\"></sup> to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, sacrifice it in such a way that it will be accepted on your behalf.",
			"30": "<sup class=\"versenum\">30 </sup>It must be eaten that same day; leave none of it till morning.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3400BB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BB&quot;&gt;BB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3400BB\"></sup> I am the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3400BC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BC&quot;&gt;BC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3400BC\"></sup>",
			"31": "<sup class=\"versenum\">31 </sup>“Keep<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3401BD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BD&quot;&gt;BD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3401BD\"></sup> my commands and follow them.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3401BE&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BE&quot;&gt;BE&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3401BE\"></sup> I am the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.",
			"32": "<sup class=\"versenum\">32 </sup>Do not profane my holy name,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3402BF&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BF&quot;&gt;BF&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3402BF\"></sup> for I must be acknowledged as holy by the Israelites.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3402BG&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BG&quot;&gt;BG&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3402BG\"></sup> I am the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, who made you holy<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3402BH&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BH&quot;&gt;BH&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3402BH\"></sup>",
			"33": "<sup class=\"versenum\">33 </sup>and who brought you out of Egypt<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3403BI&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BI&quot;&gt;BI&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3403BI\"></sup> to be your God.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3403BJ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BJ&quot;&gt;BJ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3403BJ\"></sup> I am the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.”"
		},
		"23": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">23 </span>The <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> said to Moses,",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>“Speak to the Israelites and say to them: ‘These are my appointed festivals,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3405A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3405A\"></sup> the appointed festivals of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, which you are to proclaim as sacred assemblies.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3405B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3405B\"></sup>",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>“‘There are six days when you may work,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3406C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3406C\"></sup> but the seventh day is a day of sabbath rest,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3406D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3406D\"></sup> a day of sacred assembly. You are not to do any work;<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3406E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3406E\"></sup> wherever you live, it is a sabbath to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>“‘These are the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>’s appointed festivals, the sacred assemblies you are to proclaim at their appointed times:<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3407G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3407G\"></sup>",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>The <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>’s Passover<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3408H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3408H\"></sup> begins at twilight on the fourteenth day of the first month.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3408I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3408I\"></sup>",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>On the fifteenth day of that month the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>’s Festival of Unleavened Bread<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3409J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3409J\"></sup> begins; for seven days<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3409K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3409K\"></sup> you must eat bread made without yeast.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>On the first day hold a sacred assembly<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3410L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3410L\"></sup> and do no regular work.",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>For seven days present a food offering to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3411M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3411M\"></sup> And on the seventh day hold a sacred assembly and do no regular work.’”",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>The <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> said to Moses,",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>“Speak to the Israelites and say to them: ‘When you enter the land I am going to give you<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3413N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3413N\"></sup> and you reap its harvest,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3413O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3413O\"></sup> bring to the priest a sheaf<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3413P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3413P\"></sup> of the first grain you harvest.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3413Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3413Q\"></sup>",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>He is to wave the sheaf before the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3414R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3414R\"></sup> so it will be accepted<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3414S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3414S\"></sup> on your behalf; the priest is to wave it on the day after the Sabbath.",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>On the day you wave the sheaf, you must sacrifice as a burnt offering to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> a lamb a year old<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3415T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3415T\"></sup> without defect,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3415U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3415U\"></sup>",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>together with its grain offering<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3416V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3416V\"></sup> of two-tenths of an ephah<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3416W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3416W\"></sup> of the finest flour mixed with olive oil—a food offering presented to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, a pleasing aroma—and its drink offering<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3416X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3416X\"></sup> of a quarter of a hin of wine.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3416Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3416Y\"></sup>",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>You must not eat any bread, or roasted or new grain,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3417Z&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Z&quot;&gt;Z&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3417Z\"></sup> until the very day you bring this offering to your God.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3417AA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AA&quot;&gt;AA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3417AA\"></sup> This is to be a lasting ordinance for the generations to come,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3417AB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AB&quot;&gt;AB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3417AB\"></sup> wherever you live.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3417AC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AC&quot;&gt;AC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3417AC\"></sup>",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>“‘From the day after the Sabbath, the day you brought the sheaf of the wave offering, count off seven full weeks.",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>Count off fifty days up to the day after the seventh Sabbath,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3419AE&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AE&quot;&gt;AE&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3419AE\"></sup> and then present an offering of new grain to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>From wherever you live, bring two loaves made of two-tenths of an ephah<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3420AF&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AF&quot;&gt;AF&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3420AF\"></sup> of the finest flour, baked with yeast, as a wave offering of firstfruits<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3420AG&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AG&quot;&gt;AG&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3420AG\"></sup> to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>Present with this bread seven male lambs, each a year old and without defect, one young bull and two rams. They will be a burnt offering to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, together with their grain offerings and drink offerings<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3421AH&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AH&quot;&gt;AH&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3421AH\"></sup>—a food offering, an aroma pleasing to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>Then sacrifice one male goat for a sin offering and two lambs, each a year old, for a fellowship offering.",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>The priest is to wave the two lambs before the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> as a wave offering,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3423AI&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AI&quot;&gt;AI&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3423AI\"></sup> together with the bread of the firstfruits. They are a sacred offering to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> for the priest.",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>On that same day you are to proclaim a sacred assembly<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3424AJ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AJ&quot;&gt;AJ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3424AJ\"></sup> and do no regular work.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3424AK&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AK&quot;&gt;AK&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3424AK\"></sup> This is to be a lasting ordinance for the generations to come, wherever you live.",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>“‘When you reap the harvest<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3425AL&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AL&quot;&gt;AL&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3425AL\"></sup> of your land, do not reap to the very edges of your field or gather the gleanings of your harvest.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3425AM&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AM&quot;&gt;AM&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3425AM\"></sup> Leave them for the poor and for the foreigner residing among you.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3425AN&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AN&quot;&gt;AN&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3425AN\"></sup> I am the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God.’”",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>The <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> said to Moses,",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup>“Say to the Israelites: ‘On the first day of the seventh month you are to have a day of sabbath rest, a sacred assembly<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3427AP&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AP&quot;&gt;AP&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3427AP\"></sup> commemorated with trumpet blasts.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3427AQ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AQ&quot;&gt;AQ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3427AQ\"></sup>",
			"25": "<sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup>Do no regular work,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3428AR&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AR&quot;&gt;AR&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3428AR\"></sup> but present a food offering to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3428AS&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AS&quot;&gt;AS&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3428AS\"></sup>’”",
			"26": "<sup class=\"versenum\">26 </sup>The <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> said to Moses,",
			"27": "<sup class=\"versenum\">27 </sup>“The tenth day of this seventh month<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3430AU&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AU&quot;&gt;AU&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3430AU\"></sup> is the Day of Atonement.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3430AV&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AV&quot;&gt;AV&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3430AV\"></sup> Hold a sacred assembly<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3430AW&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AW&quot;&gt;AW&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3430AW\"></sup> and deny yourselves, and present a food offering to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.",
			"28": "<sup class=\"versenum\">28 </sup>Do not do any work<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3431AX&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AX&quot;&gt;AX&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3431AX\"></sup> on that day, because it is the Day of Atonement, when atonement is made for you before the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God.",
			"29": "<sup class=\"versenum\">29 </sup>Those who do not deny themselves on that day must be cut off from their people.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3432AY&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AY&quot;&gt;AY&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3432AY\"></sup>",
			"30": "<sup class=\"versenum\">30 </sup>I will destroy from among their people<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3433AZ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AZ&quot;&gt;AZ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3433AZ\"></sup> anyone who does any work on that day.",
			"31": "<sup class=\"versenum\">31 </sup>You shall do no work at all. This is to be a lasting ordinance<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3434BA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BA&quot;&gt;BA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3434BA\"></sup> for the generations to come, wherever you live.",
			"32": "<sup class=\"versenum\">32 </sup>It is a day of sabbath rest<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3435BB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BB&quot;&gt;BB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3435BB\"></sup> for you, and you must deny yourselves. From the evening of the ninth day of the month until the following evening you are to observe your sabbath.”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3435BC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BC&quot;&gt;BC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3435BC\"></sup>",
			"33": "<sup class=\"versenum\">33 </sup>The <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> said to Moses,",
			"34": "<sup class=\"versenum\">34 </sup>“Say to the Israelites: ‘On the fifteenth day of the seventh<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3437BE&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BE&quot;&gt;BE&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3437BE\"></sup> month the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>’s Festival of Tabernacles<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3437BF&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BF&quot;&gt;BF&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3437BF\"></sup> begins, and it lasts for seven days.",
			"35": "<sup class=\"versenum\">35 </sup>The first day is a sacred assembly;<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3438BG&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BG&quot;&gt;BG&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3438BG\"></sup> do no regular work.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3438BH&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BH&quot;&gt;BH&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3438BH\"></sup>",
			"36": "<sup class=\"versenum\">36 </sup>For seven days present food offerings to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, and on the eighth day hold a sacred assembly<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3439BI&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BI&quot;&gt;BI&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3439BI\"></sup> and present a food offering to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3439BJ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BJ&quot;&gt;BJ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3439BJ\"></sup> It is the closing special assembly; do no regular work.",
			"37": "<sup class=\"versenum\">37 </sup>(“‘These are the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>’s appointed festivals, which you are to proclaim as sacred assemblies for bringing food offerings to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>—the burnt offerings and grain offerings, sacrifices and drink offerings<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3440BK&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BK&quot;&gt;BK&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3440BK\"></sup> required for each day.",
			"38": "<sup class=\"versenum\">38 </sup>These offerings<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3441BL&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BL&quot;&gt;BL&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3441BL\"></sup> are in addition to those for the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>’s Sabbaths<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3441BM&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BM&quot;&gt;BM&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3441BM\"></sup> and in addition to your gifts and whatever you have vowed and all the freewill offerings<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3441BN&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BN&quot;&gt;BN&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3441BN\"></sup> you give to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.)",
			"39": "<sup class=\"versenum\">39 </sup>“‘So beginning with the fifteenth day of the seventh month, after you have gathered the crops of the land, celebrate the festival<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3442BO&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BO&quot;&gt;BO&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3442BO\"></sup> to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> for seven days;<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3442BP&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BP&quot;&gt;BP&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3442BP\"></sup> the first day is a day of sabbath rest, and the eighth day also is a day of sabbath rest.",
			"40": "<sup class=\"versenum\">40 </sup>On the first day you are to take branches<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3443BQ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BQ&quot;&gt;BQ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3443BQ\"></sup> from luxuriant trees—from palms, willows and other leafy trees<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3443BR&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BR&quot;&gt;BR&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3443BR\"></sup>—and rejoice<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3443BS&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BS&quot;&gt;BS&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3443BS\"></sup> before the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God for seven days.",
			"41": "<sup class=\"versenum\">41 </sup>Celebrate this as a festival to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> for seven days each year. This is to be a lasting ordinance for the generations to come; celebrate it in the seventh month.",
			"42": "<sup class=\"versenum\">42 </sup>Live in temporary shelters<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3445BT&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BT&quot;&gt;BT&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3445BT\"></sup> for seven days: All native-born Israelites are to live in such shelters",
			"43": "<sup class=\"versenum\">43 </sup>so your descendants will know<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3446BU&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BU&quot;&gt;BU&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3446BU\"></sup> that I had the Israelites live in temporary shelters when I brought them out of Egypt. I am the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God.’”",
			"44": "<sup class=\"versenum\">44 </sup>So Moses announced to the Israelites the appointed festivals of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>."
		},
		"24": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">24 </span>The <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> said to Moses,",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>“Command the Israelites to bring you clear oil of pressed olives for the light so that the lamps may be kept burning continually.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>Outside the curtain that shields the ark of the covenant law in the tent of meeting, Aaron is to tend the lamps before the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> from evening till morning, continually. This is to be a lasting ordinance<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3450B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3450B\"></sup> for the generations to come.",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>The lamps on the pure gold lampstand<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3451C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3451C\"></sup> before the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> must be tended continually.",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>“Take the finest flour and bake twelve loaves of bread,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3452D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3452D\"></sup> using two-tenths of an ephah<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3452E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3452E\"></sup> for each loaf.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>Arrange them in two stacks, six in each stack, on the table of pure gold<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3453F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3453F\"></sup> before the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>By each stack put some pure incense<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3454G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3454G\"></sup> as a memorial portion<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3454H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3454H\"></sup> to represent the bread and to be a food offering presented to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>This bread is to be set out before the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> regularly,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3455I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3455I\"></sup> Sabbath after Sabbath,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3455J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3455J\"></sup> on behalf of the Israelites, as a lasting covenant.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>It belongs to Aaron and his sons,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3456K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3456K\"></sup> who are to eat it in the sanctuary area,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3456L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3456L\"></sup> because it is a most holy<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3456M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3456M\"></sup> part of their perpetual share of the food offerings presented to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.”",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>Now the son of an Israelite mother and an Egyptian father went out among the Israelites, and a fight broke out in the camp between him and an Israelite.",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>The son of the Israelite woman blasphemed the Name<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3458N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3458N\"></sup> with a curse;<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3458O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3458O\"></sup> so they brought him to Moses.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3458P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3458P\"></sup> (His mother’s name was Shelomith, the daughter of Dibri the Danite.)<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3458Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3458Q\"></sup>",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>They put him in custody until the will of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> should be made clear to them.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3459R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3459R\"></sup>",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>Then the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> said to Moses:",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>“Take the blasphemer outside the camp. All those who heard him are to lay their hands on his head, and the entire assembly is to stone him.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3461S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3461S\"></sup>",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>Say to the Israelites: ‘Anyone who curses their God<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3462T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3462T\"></sup> will be held responsible;<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3462U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3462U\"></sup>",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>anyone who blasphemes<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3463V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3463V\"></sup> the name of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> is to be put to death.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3463W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3463W\"></sup> The entire assembly must stone them. Whether foreigner or native-born, when they blaspheme the Name they are to be put to death.",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>“‘Anyone who takes the life of a human being is to be put to death.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3464X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3464X\"></sup>",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>Anyone who takes the life of someone’s animal must make restitution<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3465Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3465Y\"></sup>—life for life.",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>Anyone who injures their neighbor is to be injured in the same manner:",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>fracture for fracture, eye for eye, tooth for tooth.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3467Z&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Z&quot;&gt;Z&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3467Z\"></sup> The one who has inflicted the injury must suffer the same injury.",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>Whoever kills an animal must make restitution,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3468AA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AA&quot;&gt;AA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3468AA\"></sup> but whoever kills a human being is to be put to death.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3468AB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AB&quot;&gt;AB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3468AB\"></sup>",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>You are to have the same law for the foreigner<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3469AC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AC&quot;&gt;AC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3469AC\"></sup> and the native-born.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3469AD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AD&quot;&gt;AD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3469AD\"></sup> I am the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God.’”",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>Then Moses spoke to the Israelites, and they took the blasphemer outside the camp and stoned him.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3470AE&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AE&quot;&gt;AE&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3470AE\"></sup> The Israelites did as the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> commanded Moses."
		},
		"25": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">25 </span>The <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> said to Moses at Mount Sinai,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3471A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3471A\"></sup>",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>“Speak to the Israelites and say to them: ‘When you enter the land I am going to give you, the land itself must observe a sabbath to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>For six years sow your fields, and for six years prune your vineyards and gather their crops.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3473B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3473B\"></sup>",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>But in the seventh year the land is to have a year of sabbath rest,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3474C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3474C\"></sup> a sabbath to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>. Do not sow your fields or prune your vineyards.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3474D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3474D\"></sup>",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>Do not reap what grows of itself<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3475E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3475E\"></sup> or harvest the grapes<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3475F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3475F\"></sup> of your untended vines.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3475G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3475G\"></sup> The land is to have a year of rest.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>Whatever the land yields during the sabbath year<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3476H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3476H\"></sup> will be food for you—for yourself, your male and female servants, and the hired worker and temporary resident who live among you,",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>as well as for your livestock and the wild animals<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3477I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3477I\"></sup> in your land. Whatever the land produces may be eaten.",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>“‘Count off seven sabbath years—seven times seven years—so that the seven sabbath years amount to a period of forty-nine years.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>Then have the trumpet<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3479L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3479L\"></sup> sounded everywhere on the tenth day of the seventh month;<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3479M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3479M\"></sup> on the Day of Atonement<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3479N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3479N\"></sup> sound the trumpet throughout your land.",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>Consecrate the fiftieth year and proclaim liberty<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3480O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3480O\"></sup> throughout the land to all its inhabitants. It shall be a jubilee<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3480P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3480P\"></sup> for you; each of you is to return to your family property<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3480Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3480Q\"></sup> and to your own clan.",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>The fiftieth year shall be a jubilee<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3481R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3481R\"></sup> for you; do not sow and do not reap what grows of itself or harvest the untended vines.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3481S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3481S\"></sup>",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>For it is a jubilee and is to be holy for you; eat only what is taken directly from the fields.",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>“‘In this Year of Jubilee<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3483T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3483T\"></sup> everyone is to return to their own property.",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>“‘If you sell land to any of your own people or buy land from them, do not take advantage of each other.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3484U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3484U\"></sup>",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>You are to buy from your own people on the basis of the number of years<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3485V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3485V\"></sup> since the Jubilee. And they are to sell to you on the basis of the number of years left for harvesting crops.",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>When the years are many, you are to increase the price, and when the years are few, you are to decrease the price,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3486W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3486W\"></sup> because what is really being sold to you is the number of crops.",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>Do not take advantage of each other,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3487X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3487X\"></sup> but fear your God.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3487Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3487Y\"></sup> I am the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3487Z&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Z&quot;&gt;Z&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3487Z\"></sup>",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>“‘Follow my decrees and be careful to obey my laws,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3488AA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AA&quot;&gt;AA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3488AA\"></sup> and you will live safely in the land.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3488AB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AB&quot;&gt;AB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3488AB\"></sup>",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>Then the land will yield its fruit,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3489AC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AC&quot;&gt;AC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3489AC\"></sup> and you will eat your fill and live there in safety.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3489AD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AD&quot;&gt;AD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3489AD\"></sup>",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>You may ask, “What will we eat in the seventh year<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3490AE&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AE&quot;&gt;AE&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3490AE\"></sup> if we do not plant or harvest our crops?”",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>I will send you such a blessing<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3491AF&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AF&quot;&gt;AF&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3491AF\"></sup> in the sixth year that the land will yield enough for three years.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3491AG&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AG&quot;&gt;AG&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3491AG\"></sup>",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>While you plant during the eighth year, you will eat from the old crop and will continue to eat from it until the harvest of the ninth year comes in.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3492AH&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AH&quot;&gt;AH&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3492AH\"></sup>",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>“‘The land<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3493AI&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AI&quot;&gt;AI&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3493AI\"></sup> must not be sold permanently, because the land is mine<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3493AJ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AJ&quot;&gt;AJ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3493AJ\"></sup> and you reside in my land as foreigners<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3493AK&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AK&quot;&gt;AK&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3493AK\"></sup> and strangers.",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup>Throughout the land that you hold as a possession, you must provide for the redemption<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3494AL&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AL&quot;&gt;AL&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3494AL\"></sup> of the land.",
			"25": "<sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup>“‘If one of your fellow Israelites becomes poor and sells some of their property, their nearest relative<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3495AM&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AM&quot;&gt;AM&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3495AM\"></sup> is to come and redeem<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3495AN&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AN&quot;&gt;AN&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3495AN\"></sup> what they have sold.",
			"26": "<sup class=\"versenum\">26 </sup>If, however, there is no one to redeem it for them but later on they prosper<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3496AO&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AO&quot;&gt;AO&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3496AO\"></sup> and acquire sufficient means to redeem it themselves,",
			"27": "<sup class=\"versenum\">27 </sup>they are to determine the value for the years<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3497AP&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AP&quot;&gt;AP&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3497AP\"></sup> since they sold it and refund the balance to the one to whom they sold it; they can then go back to their own property.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3497AQ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AQ&quot;&gt;AQ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3497AQ\"></sup>",
			"28": "<sup class=\"versenum\">28 </sup>But if they do not acquire the means to repay, what was sold will remain in the possession of the buyer until the Year of Jubilee. It will be returned<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3498AR&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AR&quot;&gt;AR&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3498AR\"></sup> in the Jubilee, and they can then go back to their property.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3498AS&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AS&quot;&gt;AS&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3498AS\"></sup>",
			"29": "<sup class=\"versenum\">29 </sup>“‘Anyone who sells a house in a walled city retains the right of redemption a full year after its sale. During that time the seller may redeem it.",
			"30": "<sup class=\"versenum\">30 </sup>If it is not redeemed before a full year has passed, the house in the walled city shall belong permanently to the buyer and the buyer’s descendants. It is not to be returned in the Jubilee.",
			"31": "<sup class=\"versenum\">31 </sup>But houses in villages without walls around them are to be considered as belonging to the open country. They can be redeemed, and they are to be returned in the Jubilee.",
			"32": "<sup class=\"versenum\">32 </sup>“‘The Levites always have the right to redeem their houses in the Levitical towns,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3502AT&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AT&quot;&gt;AT&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3502AT\"></sup> which they possess.",
			"33": "<sup class=\"versenum\">33 </sup>So the property of the Levites is redeemable—that is, a house sold in any town they hold—and is to be returned in the Jubilee, because the houses in the towns of the Levites are their property among the Israelites.",
			"34": "<sup class=\"versenum\">34 </sup>But the pastureland belonging to their towns must not be sold; it is their permanent possession.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3504AU&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AU&quot;&gt;AU&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3504AU\"></sup>",
			"35": "<sup class=\"versenum\">35 </sup>“‘If any of your fellow Israelites become poor<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3505AV&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AV&quot;&gt;AV&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3505AV\"></sup> and are unable to support themselves among you, help them<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3505AW&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AW&quot;&gt;AW&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3505AW\"></sup> as you would a foreigner and stranger, so they can continue to live among you.",
			"36": "<sup class=\"versenum\">36 </sup>Do not take interest<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3506AX&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AX&quot;&gt;AX&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3506AX\"></sup> or any profit from them, but fear your God,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3506AY&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AY&quot;&gt;AY&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3506AY\"></sup> so that they may continue to live among you.",
			"37": "<sup class=\"versenum\">37 </sup>You must not lend them money at interest<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3507AZ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AZ&quot;&gt;AZ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3507AZ\"></sup> or sell them food at a profit.",
			"38": "<sup class=\"versenum\">38 </sup>I am the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God, who brought you out of Egypt to give you the land of Canaan<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3508BA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BA&quot;&gt;BA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3508BA\"></sup> and to be your God.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3508BB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BB&quot;&gt;BB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3508BB\"></sup>",
			"39": "<sup class=\"versenum\">39 </sup>“‘If any of your fellow Israelites become poor and sell themselves to you, do not make them work as slaves.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3509BC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BC&quot;&gt;BC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3509BC\"></sup>",
			"40": "<sup class=\"versenum\">40 </sup>They are to be treated as hired workers<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3510BD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BD&quot;&gt;BD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3510BD\"></sup> or temporary residents among you; they are to work for you until the Year of Jubilee.",
			"41": "<sup class=\"versenum\">41 </sup>Then they and their children are to be released, and they will go back to their own clans and to the property<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3511BE&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BE&quot;&gt;BE&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3511BE\"></sup> of their ancestors.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3511BF&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BF&quot;&gt;BF&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3511BF\"></sup>",
			"42": "<sup class=\"versenum\">42 </sup>Because the Israelites are my servants, whom I brought out of Egypt,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3512BG&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BG&quot;&gt;BG&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3512BG\"></sup> they must not be sold as slaves.",
			"43": "<sup class=\"versenum\">43 </sup>Do not rule over them ruthlessly,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3513BH&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BH&quot;&gt;BH&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3513BH\"></sup> but fear your God.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3513BI&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BI&quot;&gt;BI&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3513BI\"></sup>",
			"44": "<sup class=\"versenum\">44 </sup>“‘Your male and female slaves are to come from the nations around you; from them you may buy slaves.",
			"45": "<sup class=\"versenum\">45 </sup>You may also buy some of the temporary residents living among you and members of their clans born in your country, and they will become your property.",
			"46": "<sup class=\"versenum\">46 </sup>You can bequeath them to your children as inherited property and can make them slaves for life, but you must not rule over your fellow Israelites ruthlessly.",
			"47": "<sup class=\"versenum\">47 </sup>“‘If a foreigner residing among you becomes rich and any of your fellow Israelites become poor and sell themselves<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3517BJ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BJ&quot;&gt;BJ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3517BJ\"></sup> to the foreigner or to a member of the foreigner’s clan,",
			"48": "<sup class=\"versenum\">48 </sup>they retain the right of redemption<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3518BK&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BK&quot;&gt;BK&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3518BK\"></sup> after they have sold themselves. One of their relatives<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3518BL&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BL&quot;&gt;BL&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3518BL\"></sup> may redeem them:",
			"49": "<sup class=\"versenum\">49 </sup>An uncle or a cousin or any blood relative in their clan may redeem them. Or if they prosper,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3519BM&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BM&quot;&gt;BM&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3519BM\"></sup> they may redeem themselves.",
			"50": "<sup class=\"versenum\">50 </sup>They and their buyer are to count the time from the year they sold themselves up to the Year of Jubilee.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3520BN&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BN&quot;&gt;BN&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3520BN\"></sup> The price for their release is to be based on the rate paid to a hired worker<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3520BO&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BO&quot;&gt;BO&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3520BO\"></sup> for that number of years.",
			"51": "<sup class=\"versenum\">51 </sup>If many years remain, they must pay for their redemption a larger share of the price paid for them.",
			"52": "<sup class=\"versenum\">52 </sup>If only a few years remain until the Year of Jubilee, they are to compute that and pay for their redemption accordingly.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3522BP&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BP&quot;&gt;BP&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3522BP\"></sup>",
			"53": "<sup class=\"versenum\">53 </sup>They are to be treated as workers hired from year to year; you must see to it that those to whom they owe service do not rule over them ruthlessly.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3523BQ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BQ&quot;&gt;BQ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3523BQ\"></sup>",
			"54": "<sup class=\"versenum\">54 </sup>“‘Even if someone is not redeemed in any of these ways, they and their children are to be released in the Year of Jubilee,",
			"55": "<sup class=\"versenum\">55 </sup>for the Israelites belong to me as servants. They are my servants, whom I brought out of Egypt.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3525BR&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BR&quot;&gt;BR&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3525BR\"></sup> I am the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3525BS&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BS&quot;&gt;BS&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3525BS\"></sup>"
		},
		"26": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">26 </span>“‘Do not make idols<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3526A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3526A\"></sup> or set up an image<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3526B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3526B\"></sup> or a sacred stone<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3526C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3526C\"></sup> for yourselves, and do not place a carved stone<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3526D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3526D\"></sup> in your land to bow down before it. I am the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God.",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>“‘Observe my Sabbaths<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3527E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3527E\"></sup> and have reverence for my sanctuary.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3527F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3527F\"></sup> I am the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>“‘If you follow my decrees and are careful to obey<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3528G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3528G\"></sup> my commands,",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>I will send you rain<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3529H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3529H\"></sup> in its season,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3529I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3529I\"></sup> and the ground will yield its crops and the trees their fruit.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3529J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3529J\"></sup>",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>Your threshing will continue until grape harvest and the grape harvest will continue until planting, and you will eat all the food you want<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3530K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3530K\"></sup> and live in safety in your land.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3530L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3530L\"></sup>",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>“‘I will grant peace in the land,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3531M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3531M\"></sup> and you will lie down<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3531N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3531N\"></sup> and no one will make you afraid.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3531O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3531O\"></sup> I will remove wild beasts<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3531P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3531P\"></sup> from the land, and the sword will not pass through your country.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>You will pursue your enemies,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3532Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3532Q\"></sup> and they will fall by the sword before you.",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>Five<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3533R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3533R\"></sup> of you will chase a hundred, and a hundred of you will chase ten thousand, and your enemies will fall by the sword before you.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3533S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3533S\"></sup>",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>“‘I will look on you with favor and make you fruitful and increase your numbers,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3534T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3534T\"></sup> and I will keep my covenant<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3534U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3534U\"></sup> with you.",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>You will still be eating last year’s harvest when you will have to move it out to make room for the new.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3535V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3535V\"></sup>",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>I will put my dwelling place<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3536W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3536W\"></sup> among you, and I will not abhor you.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3536X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3536X\"></sup>",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>I will walk<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3537Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3537Y\"></sup> among you and be your God,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3537Z&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Z&quot;&gt;Z&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3537Z\"></sup> and you will be my people.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3537AA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AA&quot;&gt;AA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3537AA\"></sup>",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>I am the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3538AB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AB&quot;&gt;AB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3538AB\"></sup> who brought you out of Egypt<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3538AC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AC&quot;&gt;AC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3538AC\"></sup> so that you would no longer be slaves to the Egyptians; I broke the bars of your yoke<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3538AD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AD&quot;&gt;AD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3538AD\"></sup> and enabled you to walk with heads held high.",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>“‘But if you will not listen to me and carry out all these commands,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3539AE&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AE&quot;&gt;AE&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3539AE\"></sup>",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>and if you reject my decrees and abhor my laws<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3540AF&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AF&quot;&gt;AF&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3540AF\"></sup> and fail to carry out all my commands and so violate my covenant,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3540AG&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AG&quot;&gt;AG&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3540AG\"></sup>",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>then I will do this to you: I will bring on you sudden terror, wasting diseases and fever<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3541AH&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AH&quot;&gt;AH&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3541AH\"></sup> that will destroy your sight and sap your strength.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3541AI&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AI&quot;&gt;AI&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3541AI\"></sup> You will plant seed in vain, because your enemies will eat it.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3541AJ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AJ&quot;&gt;AJ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3541AJ\"></sup>",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>I will set my face<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3542AK&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AK&quot;&gt;AK&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3542AK\"></sup> against you so that you will be defeated<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3542AL&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AL&quot;&gt;AL&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3542AL\"></sup> by your enemies;<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3542AM&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AM&quot;&gt;AM&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3542AM\"></sup> those who hate you will rule over you,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3542AN&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AN&quot;&gt;AN&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3542AN\"></sup> and you will flee even when no one is pursuing you.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3542AO&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AO&quot;&gt;AO&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3542AO\"></sup>",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>“‘If after all this you will not listen to me,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3543AP&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AP&quot;&gt;AP&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3543AP\"></sup> I will punish<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3543AQ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AQ&quot;&gt;AQ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3543AQ\"></sup> you for your sins seven times over.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3543AR&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AR&quot;&gt;AR&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3543AR\"></sup>",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>I will break down your stubborn pride<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3544AS&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AS&quot;&gt;AS&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3544AS\"></sup> and make the sky above you like iron and the ground beneath you like bronze.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3544AT&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AT&quot;&gt;AT&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3544AT\"></sup>",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>Your strength will be spent in vain,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3545AU&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AU&quot;&gt;AU&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3545AU\"></sup> because your soil will not yield its crops, nor will the trees of your land yield their fruit.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3545AV&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AV&quot;&gt;AV&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3545AV\"></sup>",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>“‘If you remain hostile<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3546AW&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AW&quot;&gt;AW&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3546AW\"></sup> toward me and refuse to listen to me, I will multiply your afflictions seven times over,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3546AX&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AX&quot;&gt;AX&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3546AX\"></sup> as your sins deserve.",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>I will send wild animals<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3547AY&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AY&quot;&gt;AY&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3547AY\"></sup> against you, and they will rob you of your children, destroy your cattle and make you so few<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3547AZ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AZ&quot;&gt;AZ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3547AZ\"></sup> in number that your roads will be deserted.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3547BA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BA&quot;&gt;BA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3547BA\"></sup>",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>“‘If in spite of these things you do not accept my correction<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3548BB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BB&quot;&gt;BB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3548BB\"></sup> but continue to be hostile toward me,",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup>I myself will be hostile<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3549BC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BC&quot;&gt;BC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3549BC\"></sup> toward you and will afflict you for your sins seven times over.",
			"25": "<sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup>And I will bring the sword<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3550BD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BD&quot;&gt;BD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3550BD\"></sup> on you to avenge<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3550BE&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BE&quot;&gt;BE&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3550BE\"></sup> the breaking of the covenant. When you withdraw into your cities, I will send a plague<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3550BF&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BF&quot;&gt;BF&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3550BF\"></sup> among you, and you will be given into enemy hands.",
			"26": "<sup class=\"versenum\">26 </sup>When I cut off your supply of bread,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3551BG&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BG&quot;&gt;BG&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3551BG\"></sup> ten women will be able to bake your bread in one oven, and they will dole out the bread by weight. You will eat, but you will not be satisfied.",
			"27": "<sup class=\"versenum\">27 </sup>“‘If in spite of this you still do not listen to me<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3552BH&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BH&quot;&gt;BH&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3552BH\"></sup> but continue to be hostile toward me,",
			"28": "<sup class=\"versenum\">28 </sup>then in my anger<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3553BI&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BI&quot;&gt;BI&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3553BI\"></sup> I will be hostile<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3553BJ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BJ&quot;&gt;BJ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3553BJ\"></sup> toward you, and I myself will punish you for your sins seven times over.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3553BK&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BK&quot;&gt;BK&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3553BK\"></sup>",
			"29": "<sup class=\"versenum\">29 </sup>You will eat<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3554BL&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BL&quot;&gt;BL&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3554BL\"></sup> the flesh of your sons and the flesh of your daughters.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3554BM&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BM&quot;&gt;BM&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3554BM\"></sup>",
			"30": "<sup class=\"versenum\">30 </sup>I will destroy your high places,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3555BN&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BN&quot;&gt;BN&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3555BN\"></sup> cut down your incense altars<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3555BO&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BO&quot;&gt;BO&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3555BO\"></sup> and pile your dead bodies on the lifeless forms of your idols,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3555BP&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BP&quot;&gt;BP&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3555BP\"></sup> and I will abhor<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3555BQ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BQ&quot;&gt;BQ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3555BQ\"></sup> you.",
			"31": "<sup class=\"versenum\">31 </sup>I will turn your cities into ruins<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3556BR&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BR&quot;&gt;BR&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3556BR\"></sup> and lay waste<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3556BS&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BS&quot;&gt;BS&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3556BS\"></sup> your sanctuaries,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3556BT&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BT&quot;&gt;BT&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3556BT\"></sup> and I will take no delight in the pleasing aroma of your offerings.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3556BU&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BU&quot;&gt;BU&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3556BU\"></sup>",
			"32": "<sup class=\"versenum\">32 </sup>I myself will lay waste the land,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3557BV&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BV&quot;&gt;BV&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3557BV\"></sup> so that your enemies who live there will be appalled.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3557BW&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BW&quot;&gt;BW&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3557BW\"></sup>",
			"33": "<sup class=\"versenum\">33 </sup>I will scatter<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3558BX&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BX&quot;&gt;BX&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3558BX\"></sup> you among the nations<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3558BY&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BY&quot;&gt;BY&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3558BY\"></sup> and will draw out my sword<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3558BZ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BZ&quot;&gt;BZ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3558BZ\"></sup> and pursue you. Your land will be laid waste,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3558CA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference CA&quot;&gt;CA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3558CA\"></sup> and your cities will lie in ruins.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3558CB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference CB&quot;&gt;CB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3558CB\"></sup>",
			"34": "<sup class=\"versenum\">34 </sup>Then the land will enjoy its sabbath years all the time that it lies desolate<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3559CC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference CC&quot;&gt;CC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3559CC\"></sup> and you are in the country of your enemies;<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3559CD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference CD&quot;&gt;CD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3559CD\"></sup> then the land will rest and enjoy its sabbaths.",
			"35": "<sup class=\"versenum\">35 </sup>All the time that it lies desolate, the land will have the rest<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3560CE&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference CE&quot;&gt;CE&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3560CE\"></sup> it did not have during the sabbaths you lived in it.",
			"36": "<sup class=\"versenum\">36 </sup>“‘As for those of you who are left, I will make their hearts so fearful in the lands of their enemies that the sound of a windblown leaf<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3561CF&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference CF&quot;&gt;CF&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3561CF\"></sup> will put them to flight.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3561CG&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference CG&quot;&gt;CG&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3561CG\"></sup> They will run as though fleeing from the sword, and they will fall, even though no one is pursuing them.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3561CH&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference CH&quot;&gt;CH&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3561CH\"></sup>",
			"37": "<sup class=\"versenum\">37 </sup>They will stumble over one another<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3562CI&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference CI&quot;&gt;CI&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3562CI\"></sup> as though fleeing from the sword, even though no one is pursuing them. So you will not be able to stand before your enemies.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3562CJ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference CJ&quot;&gt;CJ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3562CJ\"></sup>",
			"38": "<sup class=\"versenum\">38 </sup>You will perish<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3563CK&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference CK&quot;&gt;CK&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3563CK\"></sup> among the nations; the land of your enemies will devour you.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3563CL&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference CL&quot;&gt;CL&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3563CL\"></sup>",
			"39": "<sup class=\"versenum\">39 </sup>Those of you who are left will waste away in the lands of their enemies because of their sins; also because of their ancestors’<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3564CM&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference CM&quot;&gt;CM&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3564CM\"></sup> sins they will waste away.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3564CN&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference CN&quot;&gt;CN&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3564CN\"></sup>",
			"40": "<sup class=\"versenum\">40 </sup>“‘But if they will confess<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3565CO&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference CO&quot;&gt;CO&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3565CO\"></sup> their sins<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3565CP&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference CP&quot;&gt;CP&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3565CP\"></sup> and the sins of their ancestors<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3565CQ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference CQ&quot;&gt;CQ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3565CQ\"></sup>—their unfaithfulness and their hostility toward me,",
			"41": "<sup class=\"versenum\">41 </sup>which made me hostile<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3566CR&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference CR&quot;&gt;CR&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3566CR\"></sup> toward them so that I sent them into the land of their enemies—then when their uncircumcised hearts<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3566CS&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference CS&quot;&gt;CS&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3566CS\"></sup> are humbled<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3566CT&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference CT&quot;&gt;CT&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3566CT\"></sup> and they pay<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3566CU&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference CU&quot;&gt;CU&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3566CU\"></sup> for their sin,",
			"42": "<sup class=\"versenum\">42 </sup>I will remember my covenant with Jacob<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3567CV&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference CV&quot;&gt;CV&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3567CV\"></sup> and my covenant with Isaac<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3567CW&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference CW&quot;&gt;CW&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3567CW\"></sup> and my covenant with Abraham,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3567CX&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference CX&quot;&gt;CX&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3567CX\"></sup> and I will remember the land.",
			"43": "<sup class=\"versenum\">43 </sup>For the land will be deserted<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3568CY&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference CY&quot;&gt;CY&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3568CY\"></sup> by them and will enjoy its sabbaths while it lies desolate without them. They will pay for their sins because they rejected<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3568CZ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference CZ&quot;&gt;CZ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3568CZ\"></sup> my laws and abhorred my decrees.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3568DA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference DA&quot;&gt;DA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3568DA\"></sup>",
			"44": "<sup class=\"versenum\">44 </sup>Yet in spite of this, when they are in the land of their enemies,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3569DB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference DB&quot;&gt;DB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3569DB\"></sup> I will not reject them or abhor<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3569DC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference DC&quot;&gt;DC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3569DC\"></sup> them so as to destroy them completely,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3569DD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference DD&quot;&gt;DD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3569DD\"></sup> breaking my covenant<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3569DE&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference DE&quot;&gt;DE&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3569DE\"></sup> with them. I am the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> their God.",
			"45": "<sup class=\"versenum\">45 </sup>But for their sake I will remember<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3570DF&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference DF&quot;&gt;DF&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3570DF\"></sup> the covenant with their ancestors whom I brought out of Egypt<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3570DG&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference DG&quot;&gt;DG&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3570DG\"></sup> in the sight of the nations to be their God. I am the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.’”",
			"46": "<sup class=\"versenum\">46 </sup>These are the decrees, the laws and the regulations that the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> established at Mount Sinai<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3571DH&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference DH&quot;&gt;DH&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3571DH\"></sup> between himself and the Israelites through Moses.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3571DI&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference DI&quot;&gt;DI&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3571DI\"></sup>"
		},
		"27": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">27 </span>The <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> said to Moses,",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>“Speak to the Israelites and say to them: ‘If anyone makes a special vow<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3573A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3573A\"></sup> to dedicate a person to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> by giving the equivalent value,",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>set the value of a male between the ages of twenty and sixty at fifty shekels of silver, according to the sanctuary shekel;<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3574B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3574B\"></sup>",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>for a female, set her value at thirty shekels;",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>for a person between the ages of five and twenty, set the value of a male at twenty shekels<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3576C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3576C\"></sup> and of a female at ten shekels;",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>for a person between one month and five years, set the value of a male at five shekels<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3577D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3577D\"></sup> of silver and that of a female at three shekels of silver;",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>for a person sixty years old or more, set the value of a male at fifteen shekels and of a female at ten shekels.",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>If anyone making the vow is too poor to pay<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3579E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3579E\"></sup> the specified amount, the person being dedicated is to be presented to the priest, who will set the value<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3579F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3579F\"></sup> according to what the one making the vow can afford.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>“‘If what they vowed is an animal that is acceptable as an offering to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3580G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3580G\"></sup> such an animal given to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> becomes holy.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3580H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3580H\"></sup>",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>They must not exchange it or substitute a good one for a bad one, or a bad one for a good one;<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3581I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3581I\"></sup> if they should substitute one animal for another, both it and the substitute become holy.",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>If what they vowed is a ceremonially unclean animal<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3582J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3582J\"></sup>—one that is not acceptable as an offering to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>—the animal must be presented to the priest,",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>who will judge its quality as good or bad. Whatever value the priest then sets, that is what it will be.",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>If the owner wishes to redeem<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3584K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3584K\"></sup> the animal, a fifth must be added to its value.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3584L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3584L\"></sup>",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>“‘If anyone dedicates their house as something holy to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, the priest will judge its quality as good or bad. Whatever value the priest then sets, so it will remain.",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>If the one who dedicates their house wishes to redeem it,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3586M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3586M\"></sup> they must add a fifth to its value, and the house will again become theirs.",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>“‘If anyone dedicates to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> part of their family land, its value is to be set according to the amount of seed required for it—fifty shekels of silver to a homer of barley seed.",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>If they dedicate a field during the Year of Jubilee, the value that has been set remains.",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>But if they dedicate a field after the Jubilee,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3589N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3589N\"></sup> the priest will determine the value according to the number of years that remain<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3589O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3589O\"></sup> until the next Year of Jubilee, and its set value will be reduced.",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>If the one who dedicates the field wishes to redeem it,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3590P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3590P\"></sup> they must add a fifth to its value, and the field will again become theirs.",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>If, however, they do not redeem the field, or if they have sold it to someone else, it can never be redeemed.",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>When the field is released in the Jubilee,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3592Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3592Q\"></sup> it will become holy,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3592R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3592R\"></sup> like a field devoted to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>;<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3592S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3592S\"></sup> it will become priestly property.",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>“‘If anyone dedicates to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> a field they have bought, which is not part of their family land,",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>the priest will determine its value up to the Year of Jubilee,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3594T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3594T\"></sup> and the owner must pay its value on that day as something holy to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup>In the Year of Jubilee the field will revert to the person from whom it was bought,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3595U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3595U\"></sup> the one whose land it was.",
			"25": "<sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup>Every value is to be set according to the sanctuary shekel,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3596V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3596V\"></sup> twenty gerahs<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3596W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3596W\"></sup> to the shekel.",
			"26": "<sup class=\"versenum\">26 </sup>“‘No one, however, may dedicate the firstborn of an animal, since the firstborn already belongs to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>;<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3597X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3597X\"></sup> whether an ox or a sheep, it is the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>’s.",
			"27": "<sup class=\"versenum\">27 </sup>If it is one of the unclean animals,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3598Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3598Y\"></sup> it may be bought back at its set value, adding a fifth of the value to it. If it is not redeemed, it is to be sold at its set value.",
			"28": "<sup class=\"versenum\">28 </sup>“‘But nothing that a person owns and devotes<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3599Z&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Z&quot;&gt;Z&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3599Z\"></sup> to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>—whether a human being or an animal or family land—may be sold or redeemed; everything so devoted is most holy<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3599AA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AA&quot;&gt;AA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3599AA\"></sup> to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.",
			"29": "<sup class=\"versenum\">29 </sup>“‘No person devoted to destruction may be ransomed; they are to be put to death.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3600AB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AB&quot;&gt;AB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3600AB\"></sup>",
			"30": "<sup class=\"versenum\">30 </sup>“‘A tithe<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3601AC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AC&quot;&gt;AC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3601AC\"></sup> of everything from the land, whether grain from the soil or fruit from the trees, belongs to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>; it is holy<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3601AD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AD&quot;&gt;AD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3601AD\"></sup> to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.",
			"31": "<sup class=\"versenum\">31 </sup>Whoever would redeem<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3602AE&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AE&quot;&gt;AE&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3602AE\"></sup> any of their tithe must add a fifth of the value<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3602AF&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AF&quot;&gt;AF&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3602AF\"></sup> to it.",
			"32": "<sup class=\"versenum\">32 </sup>Every tithe of the herd and flock—every tenth animal that passes under the shepherd’s rod<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3603AG&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AG&quot;&gt;AG&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3603AG\"></sup>—will be holy to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.",
			"33": "<sup class=\"versenum\">33 </sup>No one may pick out the good from the bad or make any substitution.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3604AH&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AH&quot;&gt;AH&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3604AH\"></sup> If anyone does make a substitution, both the animal and its substitute become holy and cannot be redeemed.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3604AI&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AI&quot;&gt;AI&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3604AI\"></sup>’”",
			"34": "<sup class=\"versenum\">34 </sup>These are the commands the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> gave Moses at Mount Sinai<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3605AJ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AJ&quot;&gt;AJ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3605AJ\"></sup> for the Israelites.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3605AK&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AK&quot;&gt;AK&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3605AK\"></sup>"
		}
	}
};
module.exports = book;